<book id="PRO"><id id="PRO">Proverbs
</id><h>((Proverbs))
</h><toc level="1">\begin{signline}The Proverbs\end{signline}
</toc><toc level="2">((Proverbs))
</toc><toc level="3">((Pro))
<!--currentProgress-->
</toc><p sfm="mt">The Proverbs
</p><c id="1" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.1.1" /> \begin{signline}The proverbs of Solomon the son of David, king of Israel;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.1.2" /> \begin{signline}To know wisdom and instruction; to perceive the words of understanding;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.1.3" /> \begin{signline}To receive the instruction of wisdom, justice, and judgment, and equity;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.1.4" /> \begin{signline}To give subtilty to the simple, to the young man knowledge and discretion.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.1.5" /> \begin{signline}A wise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}will hear, and will increase learning; and a man of understanding shall attain unto wise counsels:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.1.6" /> \begin{signline}To understand a proverb, and the interpretation; the words of the wise, and their dark sayings.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="7" bcv="PRO.1.7" />\begin{signline}¶ The fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the beginning of knowledge:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}fools despise wisdom and instruction.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.1.8" /> \begin{signline}My son, hear the instruction of thy father, and forsake not the law of thy mother:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.1.9" />\begin{signline}For they\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an ornament of grace unto thy head, and chains about thy neck.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="10" bcv="PRO.1.10" />\begin{signline}¶ My son, if sinners entice thee, consent thou not.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.1.11" /> \begin{signline}If they say, Come with us, let us lay wait for blood, let us lurk privily for the innocent without cause:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.1.12" /> \begin{signline}Let us swallow them up alive as the grave; and whole, as those that go down into the pit:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.1.13" /> \begin{signline}We shall find all precious substance, we shall fill our houses with spoil:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.1.14" /> \begin{signline}Cast in thy lot among us; let us all have one purse:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.1.15" /> \begin{signline}My son, walk not thou in the way with them; refrain thy foot from their path:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.1.16" /> \begin{signline}For their feet run to evil, and make haste to shed blood.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.1.17" /> \begin{signline}Surely in vain the net is spread in the sight of any bird.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.1.18" /> \begin{signline}And they lay wait for their\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}own\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}blood; they lurk privily for their\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}own\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}lives.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.1.19" />\begin{signline}So\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the ways of every one that is greedy of gain;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}taketh away the life of the owners thereof.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="20" bcv="PRO.1.20" />\begin{signline}¶ Wisdom crieth without; she uttereth her voice in the streets:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.1.21" /> \begin{signline}She crieth in the chief place of concourse, in the openings of the gates: in the city she uttereth her words,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}saying\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline},\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.1.22" /> \begin{signline}How long, ye simple ones, will ye love simplicity? and the scorners delight in their scorning, and fools hate knowledge?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.1.23" /> \begin{signline}Turn you at my reproof: behold, I will pour out my spirit unto you, I will make known my words unto you.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="24" bcv="PRO.1.24" />\begin{signline}¶ Because I have called, and ye refused; I have stretched out my hand, and no man regarded;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.1.25" /> \begin{signline}But ye have set at nought all my counsel, and would none of my reproof:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.1.26" /> \begin{signline}I also will laugh at your calamity; I will mock when your fear cometh;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.1.27" /> \begin{signline}When your fear cometh as desolation, and your destruction cometh as a whirlwind; when distress and anguish cometh  upon you.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.1.28" /> \begin{signline}Then shall they call upon me, but I will not answer; they shall seek me early, but they shall not find me:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="29" bcv="PRO.1.29" /> \begin{signline}For that they hated knowledge, and did not choose the fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="30" bcv="PRO.1.30" /> \begin{signline}They would none of my counsel: they despised all my reproof.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="31" bcv="PRO.1.31" /> \begin{signline}Therefore shall they eat of the fruit of their own way, and be filled with their own devices.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="32" bcv="PRO.1.32" /> \begin{signline}For the turning away of the simple shall slay them, and the prosperity of fools shall destroy them.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="33" bcv="PRO.1.33" /> \begin{signline}But whoso hearkeneth unto me shall dwell safely, and shall be quiet from fear of evil.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="2" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.2.1" /> \begin{signline}My son, if thou wilt receive my words, and hide my commandments with thee;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.2.2" /> \begin{signline}So that thou incline thine ear unto wisdom,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}apply thine heart to understanding;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.2.3" /> \begin{signline}Yea, if thou criest after knowledge,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}liftest up thy voice for understanding;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.2.4" /> \begin{signline}If thou seekest her as silver, and searchest for her as\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hid treasures;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.2.5" /> \begin{signline}Then shalt thou understand the fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and find the knowledge of God.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.2.6" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}giveth wisdom: out of his mouth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}cometh\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}knowledge and understanding.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.2.7" /> \begin{signline}He layeth up sound wisdom for the righteous:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a buckler to them that walk uprightly.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.2.8" /> \begin{signline}He keepeth the paths of judgment, and preserveth the way of his saints.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.2.9" /> \begin{signline}Then shalt thou understand righteousness, and judgment, and equity;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yea\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, every good path.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="10" bcv="PRO.2.10" />\begin{signline}¶ When wisdom entereth into thine heart, and knowledge is pleasant unto thy soul;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.2.11" /> \begin{signline}Discretion shall preserve thee, understanding shall keep thee:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.2.12" /> \begin{signline}To deliver thee from the way of the evil\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, from the man that speaketh froward things;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.2.13" /> \begin{signline}Who leave the paths of uprightness, to walk in the ways of darkness;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.2.14" /> \begin{signline}Who rejoice to do evil,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}delight in the frowardness of the wicked;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.2.15" /> \begin{signline}Whose ways\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}crooked, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}they\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}froward  in their paths:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.2.16" /> \begin{signline}To deliver thee from the strange woman,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from the stranger\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}flattereth with her words;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.2.17" /> \begin{signline}Which forsaketh the guide of her youth, and forgetteth the covenant of her God.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.2.18" /> \begin{signline}For her house inclineth unto death, and her paths unto the dead.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.2.19" /> \begin{signline}None that go unto her return again, neither take they hold of the paths of life.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.2.20" /> \begin{signline}That thou mayest walk in the way of good\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and keep the paths of the righteous.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.2.21" /> \begin{signline}For the upright shall dwell in the land, and the perfect shall remain in it.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.2.22" /> \begin{signline}But the wicked shall be cut off from the earth, and the transgressors shall be rooted out of it.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="3" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.3.1" /> \begin{signline}My son, forget not my law; but let thine heart keep my commandments:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.3.2" /> \begin{signline}For length of days, and long life, and peace, shall they add to thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.3.3" /> \begin{signline}Let not mercy and truth forsake thee: bind them about thy neck; write them upon the table of thine heart:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.3.4" /> \begin{signline}So shalt thou find favour and good understanding in the sight of God and man.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="5" bcv="PRO.3.5" />\begin{signline}¶ Trust in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}with all thine heart; and lean not unto thine own understanding.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.3.6" /> \begin{signline}In all thy ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct thy paths.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="7" bcv="PRO.3.7" />\begin{signline}¶ Be not wise in thine own eyes: fear the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and depart from evil.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.3.8" /> \begin{signline}It shall be health to thy navel, and marrow to thy bones.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.3.9" /> \begin{signline}Honour the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}with thy substance, and with the firstfruits of all thine increase:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.3.10" /> \begin{signline}So shall thy barns be filled with plenty, and thy presses shall burst out with new wine.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="11" bcv="PRO.3.11" />\begin{signline}¶ My son, despise not the chastening of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; neither be weary of his correction:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.3.12" /> \begin{signline}For whom the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}loveth he correcteth; even as a father the son\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in whom\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he delighteth.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="13" bcv="PRO.3.13" />\begin{signline}¶ Happy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}findeth wisdom, and the man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}getteth understanding.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.3.14" /> \begin{signline}For the merchandise of it\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better than the merchandise of silver, and the gain thereof than fine gold.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.3.15" />\begin{signline}She\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}more precious than rubies: and all the things thou canst desire are not to be compared unto her.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.3.16" /> \begin{signline}Length of days\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in her right hand;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in her left hand riches and honour.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.3.17" /> \begin{signline}Her ways\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}ways of pleasantness, and all her paths\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}peace.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.3.18" />\begin{signline}She\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a tree of life to them that lay hold upon her: and happy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is every one\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that retaineth her.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.3.19" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}by wisdom hath founded the earth; by understanding hath he established the heavens.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.3.20" /> \begin{signline}By his knowledge the depths are broken up, and the clouds drop down the dew.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="21" bcv="PRO.3.21" />\begin{signline}¶ My son, let not them depart from thine eyes: keep sound wisdom and discretion:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.3.22" /> \begin{signline}So shall they be life unto thy soul, and grace to thy neck.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.3.23" /> \begin{signline}Then shalt thou walk in thy way safely, and thy foot shall not stumble.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.3.24" /> \begin{signline}When thou liest down, thou shalt not be afraid: yea, thou shalt lie down, and thy sleep shall be sweet.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.3.25" /> \begin{signline}Be not afraid of sudden fear, neither of the desolation of the wicked, when it cometh.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.3.26" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall be thy confidence, and shall keep thy foot from being taken.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="27" bcv="PRO.3.27" />\begin{signline}¶ Withhold not good from them to whom it is due, when it is in the power of thine hand to do\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.3.28" /> \begin{signline}Say not unto thy neighbour, Go, and come again, and to morrow I will give; when thou hast it by thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="29" bcv="PRO.3.29" /> \begin{signline}Devise not evil against thy neighbour, seeing he dwelleth securely by thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="30" bcv="PRO.3.30" />\begin{signline}¶ Strive not with a man without cause, if he have done thee no harm.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="31" bcv="PRO.3.31" />\begin{signline}¶ Envy thou not the oppressor, and choose none of his ways.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="32" bcv="PRO.3.32" /> \begin{signline}For the froward\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}abomination to the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: but his secret\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with the righteous.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="33" bcv="PRO.3.33" />\begin{signline}¶ The curse of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the house of the wicked: but he blesseth the habitation of the just.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="34" bcv="PRO.3.34" /> \begin{signline}Surely he scorneth the scorners: but he giveth grace unto the lowly.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="35" bcv="PRO.3.35" /> \begin{signline}The wise shall inherit glory: but shame shall be the promotion of fools.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="4" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.4.1" /> \begin{signline}Hear, ye children, the instruction of a father, and attend to know understanding.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.4.2" /> \begin{signline}For I give you good doctrine, forsake ye not my law.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.4.3" /> \begin{signline}For I was my father’s son, tender and only\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}beloved\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the sight of my mother.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.4.4" /> \begin{signline}He taught me also, and said unto me, Let thine heart retain my words: keep my commandments, and live.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.4.5" /> \begin{signline}Get wisdom, get understanding: forget\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not; neither decline from the words of my mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.4.6" /> \begin{signline}Forsake her not, and she shall preserve thee: love her, and she shall keep thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.4.7" /> \begin{signline}Wisdom\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the principal thing;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}therefore\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}get wisdom: and with all thy getting get understanding.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.4.8" /> \begin{signline}Exalt her, and she shall promote thee: she shall bring thee to honour, when thou dost embrace her.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.4.9" /> \begin{signline}She shall give to thine head an ornament of grace: a crown of glory shall she deliver to thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.4.10" /> \begin{signline}Hear, O my son, and receive my sayings; and the years of thy life shall be many.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.4.11" /> \begin{signline}I have taught thee in the way of wisdom; I have led thee in right paths.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.4.12" /> \begin{signline}When thou goest, thy steps shall not be straitened; and when thou runnest, thou shalt not stumble.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.4.13" /> \begin{signline}Take fast hold of instruction; let\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}her\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not go: keep her; for she\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy life.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="14" bcv="PRO.4.14" />\begin{signline}¶ Enter not into the path of the wicked, and go not in the way of evil\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.4.15" /> \begin{signline}Avoid it, pass not by it, turn from it, and pass away.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.4.16" /> \begin{signline}For they sleep not, except they have done mischief; and their sleep is taken away, unless they cause\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}some\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to fall.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.4.17" /> \begin{signline}For they eat the bread of wickedness, and drink the wine of violence.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.4.18" /> \begin{signline}But the path of the just\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as the shining light, that shineth more and more unto the perfect day.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.4.19" /> \begin{signline}The way of the wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as darkness: they know not at what they stumble.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="20" bcv="PRO.4.20" />\begin{signline}¶ My son, attend to my words; incline thine ear unto my sayings.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.4.21" /> \begin{signline}Let them not depart from thine eyes; keep them in the midst of thine heart.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.4.22" />\begin{signline}For they\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}life unto those that find them, and health to all their flesh.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="23" bcv="PRO.4.23" />\begin{signline}¶ Keep thy heart with all diligence; for out of it\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the issues of life.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.4.24" /> \begin{signline}Put away from thee a froward mouth, and perverse lips put far from thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.4.25" /> \begin{signline}Let thine eyes look right on, and let thine eyelids look straight before thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.4.26" /> \begin{signline}Ponder the path of thy feet, and let all thy ways be established.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.4.27" /> \begin{signline}Turn not to the right hand nor to the left: remove thy foot from evil.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="5" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.5.1" /> \begin{signline}My son, attend unto my wisdom,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}bow thine ear to my understanding:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.5.2" /> \begin{signline}That thou mayest regard discretion, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thy lips may keep knowledge.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="3" bcv="PRO.5.3" />\begin{signline}¶ For the lips of a strange woman drop\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an honeycomb, and her mouth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}smoother than oil:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.5.4" /> \begin{signline}But her end is bitter as wormwood, sharp as a twoedged sword.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.5.5" /> \begin{signline}Her feet go down to death; her steps take hold on hell.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.5.6" /> \begin{signline}Lest thou shouldest ponder the path of life, her ways are moveable,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou canst not know\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.5.7" /> \begin{signline}Hear me now therefore, O ye children, and depart not from the words of my mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.5.8" /> \begin{signline}Remove thy way far from her, and come not nigh the door of her house:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.5.9" /> \begin{signline}Lest thou give thine honour unto others, and thy years unto the cruel:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.5.10" /> \begin{signline}Lest strangers be filled with thy wealth; and thy labours\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the house of a stranger;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.5.11" /> \begin{signline}And thou mourn at the last, when thy flesh and thy body are consumed,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.5.12" /> \begin{signline}And say, How have I hated instruction, and my heart despised reproof;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.5.13" /> \begin{signline}And have not obeyed the voice of my teachers, nor inclined mine ear to them that instructed me!\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.5.14" /> \begin{signline}I was almost in all evil in the midst of the congregation and assembly.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="15" bcv="PRO.5.15" />\begin{signline}¶ Drink waters out of thine own cistern, and running waters out of thine own well.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.5.16" /> \begin{signline}Let thy fountains be dispersed abroad,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}rivers of waters in the streets.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.5.17" /> \begin{signline}Let them be only thine own, and not strangers’ with thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.5.18" /> \begin{signline}Let thy fountain be blessed: and rejoice with the wife of thy youth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.5.19" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Let her be as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the loving hind and pleasant roe; let her breasts satisfy thee at all times; and be thou ravished always with her love.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.5.20" /> \begin{signline}And why wilt thou, my son, be ravished with a strange woman, and embrace the bosom of a stranger?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.5.21" /> \begin{signline}For the ways of man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}before the eyes of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and he pondereth all his goings.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="22" bcv="PRO.5.22" />\begin{signline}¶ His own iniquities shall take the wicked himself, and he shall be holden with the cords of his sins.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.5.23" /> \begin{signline}He shall die without instruction; and in the greatness of his folly he shall go astray.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="6" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.6.1" /> \begin{signline}My son, if thou be surety for thy friend,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}if\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou hast stricken thy hand with a stranger,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.6.2" /> \begin{signline}Thou art snared with the words of thy mouth, thou art taken with the words of thy mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.6.3" /> \begin{signline}Do this now, my son, and deliver thyself, when thou art come into the hand of thy friend; go, humble thyself, and make sure thy friend.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.6.4" /> \begin{signline}Give not sleep to thine eyes, nor slumber to thine eyelids.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.6.5" /> \begin{signline}Deliver thyself as a roe from the hand\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}of the hunter\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and as a bird from the hand of the fowler.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="6" bcv="PRO.6.6" />\begin{signline}¶ Go to the ant, thou sluggard; consider her ways, and be wise:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.6.7" /> \begin{signline}Which having no guide, overseer, or ruler,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.6.8" /> \begin{signline}Provideth her meat in the summer,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}gathereth her food in the harvest.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.6.9" /> \begin{signline}How long wilt thou sleep, O sluggard? when wilt thou arise out of thy sleep?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.6.10" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Yet\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a little sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands to sleep:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.6.11" /> \begin{signline}So shall thy poverty come as one that travelleth, and thy want as an armed man.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="12" bcv="PRO.6.12" />\begin{signline}¶ A naughty person, a wicked man, walketh with a froward mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.6.13" /> \begin{signline}He winketh with his eyes, he speaketh with his feet, he teacheth with his fingers;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.6.14" /> \begin{signline}Frowardness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in his heart, he deviseth mischief continually; he soweth discord.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.6.15" /> \begin{signline}Therefore shall his calamity come suddenly; suddenly shall he be broken without remedy.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="16" bcv="PRO.6.16" />\begin{signline}¶ These six\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}doth the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hate: yea, seven\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an abomination unto him:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.6.17" /> \begin{signline}A proud look, a lying tongue, and hands that shed innocent blood,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.6.18" /> \begin{signline}An heart that deviseth wicked imaginations, feet that be swift in running to mischief,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.6.19" /> \begin{signline}A false witness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}speaketh lies, and he that soweth discord among brethren.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="20" bcv="PRO.6.20" />\begin{signline}¶ My son, keep thy father’s commandment, and forsake not the law of thy mother:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.6.21" /> \begin{signline}Bind them continually upon thine heart,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}tie them about thy neck.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.6.22" /> \begin{signline}When thou goest, it shall lead thee; when thou sleepest, it shall keep thee; and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou awakest, it shall talk with thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.6.23" /> \begin{signline}For the commandment\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a lamp; and the law\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}light; and reproofs of instruction\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the way of life:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.6.24" /> \begin{signline}To keep thee from the evil woman, from the flattery of the tongue of a strange woman.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.6.25" /> \begin{signline}Lust not after her beauty in thine heart; neither let her take thee with her eyelids.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.6.26" /> \begin{signline}For by means of a whorish woman\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}a man is brought\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to a piece of bread: and the adulteress will hunt for the precious life.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.6.27" /> \begin{signline}Can a man take fire in his bosom, and his clothes not be burned?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.6.28" /> \begin{signline}Can one go upon hot coals, and his feet not be burned?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="29" bcv="PRO.6.29" /> \begin{signline}So he that goeth in to his neighbour’s wife; whosoever toucheth her shall not be innocent.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="30" bcv="PRO.6.30" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}do not despise a thief, if he steal to satisfy his soul when he is hungry;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="31" bcv="PRO.6.31" />\begin{signline}But\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}if\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he be found, he shall restore sevenfold; he shall give all the substance of his house.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="32" bcv="PRO.6.32" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}But\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}whoso committeth adultery with a woman lacketh understanding: he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}doeth it destroyeth his own soul.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="33" bcv="PRO.6.33" /> \begin{signline}A wound and dishonour shall he get; and his reproach shall not be wiped away.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="34" bcv="PRO.6.34" /> \begin{signline}For jealousy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the rage of a man: therefore he will not spare in the day of vengeance.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="35" bcv="PRO.6.35" /> \begin{signline}He will not regard any ransom; neither will he rest content, though thou givest many gifts.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="7" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.7.1" /> \begin{signline}My son, keep my words, and lay up my commandments with thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.7.2" /> \begin{signline}Keep my commandments, and live; and my law as the apple of thine eye.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.7.3" /> \begin{signline}Bind them upon thy fingers, write them upon the table of thine heart.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.7.4" /> \begin{signline}Say unto wisdom, Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}my sister; and call understanding\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thy\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}kinswoman:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.7.5" /> \begin{signline}That they may keep thee from the strange woman, from the stranger\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}flattereth with her words.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="6" bcv="PRO.7.6" />\begin{signline}¶ For at the window of my house I looked through my casement,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.7.7" /> \begin{signline}And beheld among the simple ones, I discerned among the youths, a young man void of understanding,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.7.8" /> \begin{signline}Passing through the street near her corner; and he went the way to her house,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.7.9" /> \begin{signline}In the twilight, in the evening, in the black and dark night:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.7.10" /> \begin{signline}And, behold, there met him a woman\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the attire of an harlot, and subtil of heart.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.7.11" />\begin{signline}(She\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}loud and stubborn; her feet abide not in her house:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.7.12" /> \begin{signline}Now\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is she\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}without, now in the streets, and lieth in wait at every corner.)\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.7.13" /> \begin{signline}So she caught him, and kissed him,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with an impudent face said unto him,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.7.14" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}I have\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}peace offerings with me; this day have I payed my vows.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.7.15" /> \begin{signline}Therefore came I forth to meet thee, diligently to seek thy face, and I have found thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.7.16" /> \begin{signline}I have decked my bed with coverings of tapestry, with carved\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}works\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, with fine linen of Egypt.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.7.17" /> \begin{signline}I have perfumed my bed with myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.7.18" /> \begin{signline}Come, let us take our fill of love until the morning: let us solace ourselves with loves.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.7.19" /> \begin{signline}For the goodman\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not at home, he is gone a long journey:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.7.20" /> \begin{signline}He hath taken a bag of money with him,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}will come home at the day appointed.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.7.21" /> \begin{signline}With her much fair speech she caused him to yield, with the flattering of her lips she forced him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.7.22" /> \begin{signline}He goeth after her straightway, as an ox goeth to the slaughter, or as a fool to the correction of the stocks;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.7.23" /> \begin{signline}Till a dart strike through his liver; as a bird hasteth to the snare, and knoweth not that it\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for his life.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="24" bcv="PRO.7.24" />\begin{signline}¶ Hearken unto me now therefore, O ye children, and attend to the words of my mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.7.25" /> \begin{signline}Let not thine heart decline to her ways, go not astray in her paths.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.7.26" /> \begin{signline}For she hath cast down many wounded: yea, many strong\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}have been slain by her.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.7.27" /> \begin{signline}Her house\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the way to hell, going down to the chambers of death.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="8" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.8.1" /> \begin{signline}Doth not wisdom cry? and understanding put forth her voice?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.8.2" /> \begin{signline}She standeth in the top of high places, by the way in the places of the paths.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.8.3" /> \begin{signline}She crieth at the gates, at the entry of the city, at the coming in at the doors.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.8.4" /> \begin{signline}Unto you, O men, I call; and my voice\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to the sons of man.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.8.5" /> \begin{signline}O ye simple, understand wisdom: and, ye fools, be ye of an understanding heart.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.8.6" /> \begin{signline}Hear; for I will speak of excellent things; and the opening of my lips\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}right things.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.8.7" /> \begin{signline}For my mouth shall speak truth; and wickedness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an abomination to my lips.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.8.8" /> \begin{signline}All the words of my mouth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in righteousness;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}nothing froward or perverse in them.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.8.9" />\begin{signline}They\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all plain to him that understandeth, and right to them that find knowledge.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.8.10" /> \begin{signline}Receive my instruction, and not silver; and knowledge rather than choice gold.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.8.11" /> \begin{signline}For wisdom\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better than rubies; and all the things that may be desired are not to be compared to it.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="12" bcv="PRO.8.12" /> \begin{signline}I wisdom dwell with prudence, and find out knowledge of witty inventions.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.8.13" /> \begin{signline}The fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to hate evil: pride, and arrogancy, and the evil way, and the froward mouth, do I hate.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.8.14" /> \begin{signline}Counsel\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mine, and sound wisdom: I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}understanding; I have strength.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.8.15" /> \begin{signline}By me kings reign, and princes decree justice.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.8.16" /> \begin{signline}By me princes rule, and nobles,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}all the judges of the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.8.17" /> \begin{signline}I love them that love me; and those that seek me early shall find me.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.8.18" /> \begin{signline}Riches and honour\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with me;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yea\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, durable riches and righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.8.19" /> \begin{signline}My fruit\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better than gold, yea, than fine gold; and my revenue than choice silver.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.8.20" /> \begin{signline}I lead in the way of righteousness, in the midst of the paths of judgment:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.8.21" /> \begin{signline}That I may cause those that love me to inherit substance; and I will fill their treasures.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="22" bcv="PRO.8.22" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}possessed me in the beginning of his way, before his works of old.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.8.23" /> \begin{signline}I was set up from everlasting, from the beginning, or ever the earth was.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.8.24" />\begin{signline}When\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there were\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no depths, I was brought forth; when\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there were\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no fountains abounding with water.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.8.25" /> \begin{signline}Before the mountains were settled, before the hills was I brought forth:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.8.26" /> \begin{signline}While as yet he had not made the earth, nor the fields, nor the highest part of the dust of the world.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.8.27" /> \begin{signline}When he prepared the heavens, I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}was\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}there: when he set a compass upon the face of the depth:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.8.28" /> \begin{signline}When he established the clouds above: when he strengthened the fountains of the deep:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="29" bcv="PRO.8.29" /> \begin{signline}When he gave to the sea his decree, that the waters should not pass his commandment: when he appointed the foundations of the earth:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="30" bcv="PRO.8.30" /> \begin{signline}Then I was by him,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}one brought up\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with him:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}and I was daily\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}delight, rejoicing always before him;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="31" bcv="PRO.8.31" /> \begin{signline}Rejoicing in the habitable part of his earth; and my delights\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}were\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with the sons of men.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="32" bcv="PRO.8.32" /> \begin{signline}Now therefore hearken unto me, O ye children: for blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are they that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}keep my ways.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="33" bcv="PRO.8.33" /> \begin{signline}Hear instruction, and be wise, and refuse it not.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="34" bcv="PRO.8.34" /> \begin{signline}Blessed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the man that heareth me, watching daily at my gates, waiting at the posts of my doors.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="35" bcv="PRO.8.35" /> \begin{signline}For whoso findeth me findeth life, and shall obtain favour of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="36" bcv="PRO.8.36" /> \begin{signline}But he that sinneth against me wrongeth his own soul: all they that hate me love death.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="9" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.9.1" /> \begin{signline}Wisdom hath builded her house, she hath hewn out her seven pillars:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.9.2" /> \begin{signline}She hath killed her beasts; she hath mingled her wine; she hath also furnished her table.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.9.3" /> \begin{signline}She hath sent forth her maidens: she crieth upon the highest places of the city,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.9.4" />\begin{signline}Whoso\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}simple, let him turn in hither:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}him that wanteth understanding, she saith to him,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.9.5" /> \begin{signline}Come, eat of my bread, and drink of the wine\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I have mingled.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.9.6" /> \begin{signline}Forsake the foolish, and live; and go in the way of understanding.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.9.7" /> \begin{signline}He that reproveth a scorner getteth to himself shame: and he that rebuketh a wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man getteth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}himself a blot.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.9.8" /> \begin{signline}Reprove not a scorner, lest he hate thee: rebuke a wise man, and he will love thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.9.9" /> \begin{signline}Give\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}instruction\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to a wise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and he will be yet wiser: teach a just\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and he will increase in learning.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.9.10" /> \begin{signline}The fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the beginning of wisdom: and the knowledge of the holy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}understanding.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.9.11" /> \begin{signline}For by me thy days shall be multiplied, and the years of thy life shall be increased.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.9.12" /> \begin{signline}If thou be wise, thou shalt be wise for thyself: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}if\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou scornest, thou alone shalt bear\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="13" bcv="PRO.9.13" />\begin{signline}¶ A foolish woman\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}clamorous:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}she is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}simple, and knoweth nothing.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.9.14" /> \begin{signline}For she sitteth at the door of her house, on a seat in the high places of the city,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.9.15" /> \begin{signline}To call passengers who go right on their ways:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.9.16" />\begin{signline}Whoso\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}simple, let him turn in hither: and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}him that wanteth understanding, she saith to him,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.9.17" /> \begin{signline}Stolen waters are sweet, and bread\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}eaten\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in secret is pleasant.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.9.18" /> \begin{signline}But he knoweth not that the dead\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}there;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}her guests\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the depths of hell.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="10" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.10.1" /> \begin{signline}The proverbs of Solomon. A wise son maketh a glad father: but a foolish son\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the heaviness of his mother.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="2" bcv="PRO.10.2" /> \begin{signline}Treasures of wickedness profit nothing: but righteousness delivereth  from death.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.10.3" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will not suffer the soul of the righteous to famish: but he casteth away the substance of the wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.10.4" /> \begin{signline}He becometh poor that dealeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a slack hand: but the hand of the diligent maketh rich.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.10.5" /> \begin{signline}He that gathereth in summer\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a wise son:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that sleepeth in harvest\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a son that causeth shame.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.10.6" /> \begin{signline}Blessings\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon the head of the just: but violence covereth the mouth of the wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.10.7" /> \begin{signline}The memory of the just\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}blessed: but the name of the wicked shall rot.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.10.8" /> \begin{signline}The wise in heart will receive commandments: but a prating fool shall fall.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.10.9" /> \begin{signline}He that walketh uprightly walketh surely: but he that perverteth his ways shall be known.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.10.10" /> \begin{signline}He that winketh with the eye causeth  sorrow: but a prating fool shall fall.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.10.11" /> \begin{signline}The mouth of a righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a well of life: but violence covereth the mouth of the wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.10.12" /> \begin{signline}Hatred stirreth up strifes: but love covereth all sins.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.10.13" /> \begin{signline}In the lips of him that hath understanding wisdom is found: but a rod\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for the back of him that is void of understanding.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.10.14" /> \begin{signline}Wise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}lay up knowledge: but the mouth of the foolish\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}near destruction.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.10.15" /> \begin{signline}The rich man’s wealth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his strong city: the destruction of the poor\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their poverty.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.10.16" /> \begin{signline}The labour of the righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}tendeth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to life: the fruit of the wicked to sin.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.10.17" />\begin{signline}He\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the way of life that keepeth instruction: but he that refuseth reproof erreth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.10.18" /> \begin{signline}He that hideth hatred\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}lying lips, and he that uttereth a slander,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a fool.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.10.19" /> \begin{signline}In the multitude of words there wanteth not sin: but he that refraineth his lips\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wise.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="20" bcv="PRO.10.20" /> \begin{signline}The tongue of the just\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}choice silver: the heart of the wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}little worth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.10.21" /> \begin{signline}The lips of the righteous feed many: but fools die for want of wisdom.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.10.22" /> \begin{signline}The blessing of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, it maketh rich, and he addeth no sorrow with it.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.10.23" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as sport to a fool to do mischief: but a man of understanding hath wisdom.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="24" bcv="PRO.10.24" /> \begin{signline}The fear of the wicked, it shall come upon him: but the desire of the righteous shall be granted.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.10.25" /> \begin{signline}As the whirlwind passeth, so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the wicked no\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}more:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}but the righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an everlasting foundation.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.10.26" /> \begin{signline}As vinegar to the teeth, and as smoke to the eyes, so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the sluggard to them that send him.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="27" bcv="PRO.10.27" /> \begin{signline}The fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}prolongeth days: but the years of the wicked shall be shortened.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.10.28" /> \begin{signline}The hope of the righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}gladness: but the expectation of the wicked shall perish.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="29" bcv="PRO.10.29" /> \begin{signline}The way of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}strength to the upright: but destruction\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to the workers of iniquity.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="30" bcv="PRO.10.30" /> \begin{signline}The righteous shall never be removed: but the wicked shall not inhabit the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="31" bcv="PRO.10.31" /> \begin{signline}The mouth of the just bringeth forth wisdom: but the froward tongue shall be cut out.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="32" bcv="PRO.10.32" /> \begin{signline}The lips of the righteous know what is acceptable: but the mouth of the wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}speaketh\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}frowardness.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="11" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.11.1" /> \begin{signline}A false balance\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}abomination to the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: but a just weight\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his delight.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.11.2" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}When\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}pride cometh, then cometh shame: but with the lowly\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wisdom.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.11.3" /> \begin{signline}The integrity of the upright shall guide them: but the perverseness of transgressors shall destroy them.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.11.4" /> \begin{signline}Riches profit not in the day of wrath: but righteousness delivereth from death.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="5" bcv="PRO.11.5" /> \begin{signline}The righteousness of the perfect shall direct his way: but the wicked shall fall by his own wickedness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.11.6" /> \begin{signline}The righteousness of the upright shall deliver them: but transgressors shall be taken in\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their own\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}naughtiness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.11.7" /> \begin{signline}When a wicked man dieth,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}expectation shall perish: and the hope of unjust\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}perisheth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.11.8" /> \begin{signline}The righteous is delivered out of trouble, and the wicked cometh in his stead.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.11.9" /> \begin{signline}An hypocrite with\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mouth destroyeth his neighbour: but through knowledge shall the just be delivered.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="10" bcv="PRO.11.10" /> \begin{signline}When it goeth well with the righteous, the city rejoiceth: and when the wicked perish,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shouting.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.11.11" /> \begin{signline}By the blessing of the upright the city is exalted: but it is overthrown by the mouth of the wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="12" bcv="PRO.11.12" /> \begin{signline}He that is void of wisdom despiseth his neighbour: but a man of understanding holdeth his peace.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.11.13" /> \begin{signline}A talebearer revealeth secrets: but he that is of a faithful spirit concealeth  the matter.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.11.14" /> \begin{signline}Where no counsel\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, the people fall: but in the multitude of counsellors\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}safety.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.11.15" /> \begin{signline}He that is surety for a stranger shall smart\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for it:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}and he that hateth suretiship is sure.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.11.16" /> \begin{signline}A gracious woman retaineth honour: and strong\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}retain riches.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.11.17" /> \begin{signline}The merciful man doeth good to his own soul: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}cruel troubleth his own flesh.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.11.18" /> \begin{signline}The wicked worketh a deceitful work: but to him that soweth righteousness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a sure reward.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.11.19" /> \begin{signline}As righteousness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}tendeth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to life: so he that pursueth evil\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}pursueth it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to his own death.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.11.20" /> \begin{signline}They that are of a froward heart\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}abomination to the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}such as are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upright in\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}way\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his delight.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.11.21" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Though\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hand\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}join\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in hand, the wicked shall not be unpunished: but the seed of the righteous shall be delivered.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.11.22" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}As\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a jewel of gold in a swine’s snout,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a fair woman which is without discretion.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.11.23" /> \begin{signline}The desire of the righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}only good:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the expectation of the wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wrath.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.11.24" /> \begin{signline}There is that scattereth, and yet increaseth; and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that withholdeth more than is meet, but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it tendeth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to poverty.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.11.25" /> \begin{signline}The liberal soul shall be made fat: and he that watereth shall be watered also himself.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.11.26" /> \begin{signline}He that withholdeth corn, the people shall curse him: but blessing\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upon the head of him that selleth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.11.27" /> \begin{signline}He that diligently seeketh good procureth favour: but he that seeketh mischief, it shall come unto him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.11.28" /> \begin{signline}He that trusteth in his riches shall fall: but the righteous shall flourish as a branch.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="29" bcv="PRO.11.29" /> \begin{signline}He that troubleth his own house shall inherit the wind: and the fool\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}servant to the wise of heart.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="30" bcv="PRO.11.30" /> \begin{signline}The fruit of the righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a tree of life; and he that winneth souls\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wise.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="31" bcv="PRO.11.31" /> \begin{signline}Behold, the righteous shall be recompensed in the earth: much more the wicked and the sinner.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="12" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.12.1" /> \begin{signline}Whoso loveth instruction loveth knowledge: but he that hateth reproof\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}brutish.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.12.2" /> \begin{signline}A good\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}obtaineth  favour of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: but a man of wicked devices will he condemn.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.12.3" /> \begin{signline}A man shall not be established by wickedness: but the root of the righteous shall not be moved.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.12.4" /> \begin{signline}A virtuous woman\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a crown to her husband: but she that maketh ashamed\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as rottenness in his bones.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.12.5" /> \begin{signline}The thoughts of the righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}right:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the counsels of the wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}deceit.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.12.6" /> \begin{signline}The words of the wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to lie in wait for blood: but the mouth of the upright shall deliver them.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.12.7" /> \begin{signline}The wicked are overthrown, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not: but the house of the righteous shall stand.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.12.8" /> \begin{signline}A man shall be commended according to his wisdom: but he that is of a perverse heart shall be despised.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.12.9" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}He that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}despised, and hath a servant,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better than he that honoureth himself, and lacketh bread.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.12.10" /> \begin{signline}A righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}regardeth the life of his beast: but the tender mercies of the wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}cruel.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.12.11" /> \begin{signline}He that tilleth his land shall be satisfied with bread: but he that followeth vain\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}persons is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}void of understanding.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.12.12" /> \begin{signline}The wicked desireth the net of evil\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men:\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}but the root of the righteous yieldeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}fruit\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.12.13" /> \begin{signline}The wicked is snared by the transgression of\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}lips: but the just shall come out of trouble.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.12.14" /> \begin{signline}A man shall be satisfied with good by the fruit of\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mouth: and the recompence of a man’s hands shall be rendered unto him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.12.15" /> \begin{signline}The way of a fool\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}right in his own eyes: but he that hearkeneth unto counsel\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wise.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.12.16" /> \begin{signline}A fool’s wrath is presently known: but a prudent\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}covereth  shame.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.12.17" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}He that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}speaketh truth sheweth forth righteousness: but a false witness deceit.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.12.18" /> \begin{signline}There is that speaketh like the piercings of a sword: but the tongue of the wise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}health.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.12.19" /> \begin{signline}The lip of truth shall be established for ever: but a lying tongue\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}but for a moment.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.12.20" /> \begin{signline}Deceit\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the heart of them that imagine evil: but to the counsellors of peace\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}joy.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.12.21" /> \begin{signline}There shall no evil happen to the just: but the wicked shall be filled with mischief.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.12.22" /> \begin{signline}Lying lips\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}abomination to the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: but they that deal truly\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his delight.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.12.23" /> \begin{signline}A prudent man concealeth knowledge: but the heart of fools proclaimeth  foolishness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.12.24" /> \begin{signline}The hand of the diligent shall bear rule: but the slothful shall be under tribute.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.12.25" /> \begin{signline}Heaviness in the heart of man maketh it stoop: but a good word maketh it glad.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.12.26" /> \begin{signline}The righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}more excellent than his neighbour: but the way of the wicked seduceth  them.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.12.27" /> \begin{signline}The slothful\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}roasteth not that which he took in hunting: but the substance of a diligent man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}precious.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.12.28" /> \begin{signline}In the way of righteousness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}life; and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the pathway\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thereof there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no death.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="13" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.13.1" /> \begin{signline}A wise son\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}heareth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his father’s instruction: but a scorner heareth not rebuke.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.13.2" /> \begin{signline}A man shall eat good by the fruit of\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mouth: but the soul of the transgressors\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall eat\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}violence.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.13.3" /> \begin{signline}He that keepeth his mouth keepeth his life:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that openeth wide his lips shall have destruction.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.13.4" /> \begin{signline}The soul of the sluggard desireth, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}hath\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}nothing: but the soul of the diligent shall be made fat.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.13.5" /> \begin{signline}A righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hateth lying: but a wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}is loathsome, and cometh to shame.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.13.6" /> \begin{signline}Righteousness keepeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upright in the way: but wickedness overthroweth the sinner.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.13.7" /> \begin{signline}There is that maketh himself rich, yet\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}hath\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}nothing:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that maketh himself poor, yet\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}hath\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great riches.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.13.8" /> \begin{signline}The ransom of a man’s life\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his riches: but the poor heareth not rebuke.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.13.9" /> \begin{signline}The light of the righteous rejoiceth: but the lamp of the wicked shall be put out.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.13.10" /> \begin{signline}Only by pride cometh contention: but with the well advised\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wisdom.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.13.11" /> \begin{signline}Wealth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}gotten\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}by vanity shall be diminished: but he that gathereth by labour shall increase.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.13.12" /> \begin{signline}Hope deferred maketh the heart sick: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the desire cometh,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a tree of life.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.13.13" /> \begin{signline}Whoso despiseth the word shall be destroyed: but he that feareth the commandment shall be rewarded.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.13.14" /> \begin{signline}The law of the wise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a fountain of life, to depart from the snares of death.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.13.15" /> \begin{signline}Good understanding giveth favour: but the way of transgressors\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hard.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.13.16" /> \begin{signline}Every prudent\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}dealeth with knowledge: but a fool layeth open\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}folly.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.13.17" /> \begin{signline}A wicked messenger falleth into mischief: but a faithful ambassador\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}health.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.13.18" /> \begin{signline}Poverty and shame\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be to\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}him that refuseth instruction: but he that regardeth reproof shall be honoured.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.13.19" /> \begin{signline}The desire accomplished is sweet to the soul: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}abomination to fools to depart from evil.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.13.20" /> \begin{signline}He that walketh with wise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall be wise: but a companion of fools shall be destroyed.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.13.21" /> \begin{signline}Evil pursueth sinners: but to the righteous good shall be repayed.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.13.22" /> \begin{signline}A good\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}leaveth an inheritance to his children’s children: and the wealth of the sinner\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}laid up for the just.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.13.23" /> \begin{signline}Much food\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is in\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the tillage of the poor: but there is\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}destroyed for want of judgment.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.13.24" /> \begin{signline}He that spareth his rod hateth his son: but he that loveth him chasteneth him betimes.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.13.25" /> \begin{signline}The righteous eateth to the satisfying of his soul: but the belly of the wicked shall want.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="14" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.14.1" /> \begin{signline}Every wise woman buildeth her house: but the foolish plucketh it down with her hands.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.14.2" /> \begin{signline}He that walketh in his uprightness feareth the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}perverse in his ways despiseth him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.14.3" /> \begin{signline}In the mouth of the foolish\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a rod of pride: but the lips of the wise shall preserve them.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.14.4" /> \begin{signline}Where no oxen\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, the crib\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}clean: but much increase\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}by the strength of the ox.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.14.5" /> \begin{signline}A faithful witness will not lie: but a false witness will utter lies.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.14.6" /> \begin{signline}A scorner seeketh wisdom, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}findeth it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not: but knowledge\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}easy unto him that understandeth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.14.7" /> \begin{signline}Go from the presence of a foolish man, when thou perceivest not\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in him\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the lips of knowledge.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.14.8" /> \begin{signline}The wisdom of the prudent\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to understand his way: but the folly of fools\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}deceit.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.14.9" /> \begin{signline}Fools make a mock at sin: but among the righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}favour.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.14.10" /> \begin{signline}The heart knoweth his own bitterness; and a stranger doth not intermeddle with his joy.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.14.11" /> \begin{signline}The house of the wicked shall be overthrown: but the tabernacle of the upright shall flourish.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.14.12" /> \begin{signline}There is a way which seemeth right unto a man, but the end thereof\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the ways of death.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.14.13" /> \begin{signline}Even in laughter the heart is sorrowful; and the end of that mirth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}heaviness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.14.14" /> \begin{signline}The backslider in heart shall be filled with his own ways: and a good man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be satisfied\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from himself.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.14.15" /> \begin{signline}The simple believeth every word: but the prudent\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}looketh well to his going.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.14.16" /> \begin{signline}A wise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}feareth, and departeth from evil: but the fool rageth, and is confident.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.14.17" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}He that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}soon angry dealeth foolishly: and a man of wicked devices is hated.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.14.18" /> \begin{signline}The simple inherit folly: but the prudent are crowned with knowledge.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.14.19" /> \begin{signline}The evil bow before the good; and the wicked at the gates of the righteous.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.14.20" /> \begin{signline}The poor is hated even of his own neighbour: but the rich\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}hath\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}many friends.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.14.21" /> \begin{signline}He that despiseth his neighbour sinneth: but he that hath mercy on the poor, happy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.14.22" /> \begin{signline}Do they not err that devise evil? but mercy and truth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to them that devise good.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.14.23" /> \begin{signline}In all labour there is profit: but the talk of the lips\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}tendeth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}only to penury.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.14.24" /> \begin{signline}The crown of the wise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their riches:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the foolishness of fools\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}folly.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.14.25" /> \begin{signline}A true witness delivereth souls: but a deceitful\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}witness\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}speaketh lies.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="26" bcv="PRO.14.26" /> \begin{signline}In the fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}strong confidence: and his children shall have a place of refuge.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.14.27" /> \begin{signline}The fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a fountain of life, to depart from the snares of death.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.14.28" /> \begin{signline}In the multitude of people\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the king’s honour: but in the want of people\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the destruction of the prince.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="29" bcv="PRO.14.29" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}He that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}slow to wrath\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of great understanding: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hasty of spirit exalteth folly.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="30" bcv="PRO.14.30" /> \begin{signline}A sound heart\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the life of the flesh: but envy the rottenness of the bones.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="31" bcv="PRO.14.31" /> \begin{signline}He that oppresseth the poor reproacheth  his Maker: but he that honoureth him hath mercy on the poor.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="32" bcv="PRO.14.32" /> \begin{signline}The wicked is driven away in his wickedness: but the righteous hath hope in his death.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="33" bcv="PRO.14.33" /> \begin{signline}Wisdom resteth in the heart of him that hath understanding: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that which is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the midst of fools is made known.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="34" bcv="PRO.14.34" /> \begin{signline}Righteousness exalteth a nation: but sin\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a reproach to any people.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="35" bcv="PRO.14.35" /> \begin{signline}The king’s favour\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}toward a wise servant: but his wrath is\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}against\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}him that causeth shame.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="15" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.15.1" /> \begin{signline}A soft answer turneth away wrath: but grievous words stir up anger.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.15.2" /> \begin{signline}The tongue of the wise useth knowledge aright: but the mouth of fools poureth out foolishness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.15.3" /> \begin{signline}The eyes of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in every place, beholding the evil and the good.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.15.4" /> \begin{signline}A wholesome tongue\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a tree of life: but perverseness therein\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a breach in the spirit.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.15.5" /> \begin{signline}A fool despiseth his father’s instruction: but he that regardeth reproof is prudent.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.15.6" /> \begin{signline}In the house of the righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}much treasure: but in the revenues of the wicked is trouble.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.15.7" /> \begin{signline}The lips of the wise disperse knowledge: but the heart of the foolish\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}doeth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not so.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.15.8" /> \begin{signline}The sacrifice of the wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an abomination to the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: but the prayer of the upright\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his delight.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.15.9" /> \begin{signline}The way of the wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an abomination unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: but he loveth him that followeth after righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.15.10" /> \begin{signline}Correction\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}grievous unto him that forsaketh the way:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that hateth reproof shall die.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.15.11" /> \begin{signline}Hell and destruction\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}before the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: how much more then the hearts of the children of men?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.15.12" /> \begin{signline}A scorner loveth not one that reproveth him: neither will he go unto the wise.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.15.13" /> \begin{signline}A merry heart maketh a cheerful countenance: but by sorrow of the heart the spirit is broken.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.15.14" /> \begin{signline}The heart of him that hath understanding seeketh knowledge: but the mouth of fools feedeth on foolishness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.15.15" /> \begin{signline}All the days of the afflicted\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}evil: but he that is of a merry heart\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}hath\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a continual feast.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="16" bcv="PRO.15.16" /> \begin{signline}Better\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}little with the fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}than great treasure and trouble therewith.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.15.17" /> \begin{signline}Better\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a dinner of herbs where love is, than a stalled ox and hatred therewith.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.15.18" /> \begin{signline}A wrathful man stirreth up strife: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}slow to anger appeaseth strife.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.15.19" /> \begin{signline}The way of the slothful\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as an hedge of thorns: but the way of the righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}made plain.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.15.20" /> \begin{signline}A wise son maketh a glad father: but a foolish man despiseth his mother.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.15.21" /> \begin{signline}Folly\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}joy to\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}destitute of wisdom: but a man of understanding walketh  uprightly.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.15.22" /> \begin{signline}Without counsel purposes are disappointed: but in the multitude of counsellors they are established.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.15.23" /> \begin{signline}A man hath joy by the answer of his mouth: and a word\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}spoken\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in due season, how good\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}!\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.15.24" /> \begin{signline}The way of life\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}above to the wise, that he may depart from hell beneath.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.15.25" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will destroy the house of the proud: but he will establish the border of the widow.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.15.26" /> \begin{signline}The thoughts of the wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an abomination to the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}the words\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of the pure\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}pleasant words.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.15.27" /> \begin{signline}He that is greedy of gain troubleth his own house; but he that hateth gifts shall live.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.15.28" /> \begin{signline}The heart of the righteous studieth to answer: but the mouth of the wicked poureth out evil things.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="29" bcv="PRO.15.29" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}far from the wicked: but he heareth the prayer of the righteous.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="30" bcv="PRO.15.30" /> \begin{signline}The light of the eyes rejoiceth the heart:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a good report maketh the bones fat.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="31" bcv="PRO.15.31" /> \begin{signline}The ear that heareth the reproof of life abideth among the wise.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="32" bcv="PRO.15.32" /> \begin{signline}He that refuseth instruction despiseth  his own soul: but he that heareth reproof getteth understanding.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="33" bcv="PRO.15.33" /> \begin{signline}The fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the instruction of wisdom; and before honour\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}humility.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="16" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.16.1" /> \begin{signline}The preparations of the heart in man, and the answer of the tongue,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.16.2" /> \begin{signline}All the ways of a man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}clean in his own eyes; but the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}weigheth the spirits.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.16.3" /> \begin{signline}Commit thy works unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and thy thoughts shall be established.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.16.4" /> \begin{signline}The\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath made all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for himself: yea, even the wicked for the day of evil.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.16.5" />\begin{signline}Every one\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}proud in heart\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an abomination to the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}though\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hand\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}join\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in hand, he shall not be unpunished.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.16.6" /> \begin{signline}By mercy and truth iniquity is purged: and by the fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}depart from evil.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.16.7" /> \begin{signline}When a man’s ways please the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, he maketh even his enemies to be at peace with him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.16.8" /> \begin{signline}Better\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a little with righteousness than great revenues without right.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.16.9" /> \begin{signline}A man’s heart deviseth his way: but the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}directeth his steps.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.16.10" /> \begin{signline}A divine sentence\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the lips of the king: his mouth transgresseth  not in judgment.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.16.11" /> \begin{signline}A just weight and balance\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD’s\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}: all the weights of the bag\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his work.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.16.12" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an abomination to kings to commit wickedness: for the throne is established by righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.16.13" /> \begin{signline}Righteous lips\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the delight of kings; and they love him that speaketh right.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="14" bcv="PRO.16.14" /> \begin{signline}The wrath of a king\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}messengers of death: but a wise man will pacify it.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.16.15" /> \begin{signline}In the light of the king’s countenance\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}life; and his favour\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as a cloud of the latter rain.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.16.16" /> \begin{signline}How much better\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to get wisdom than gold! and to get understanding rather to be chosen than silver!\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.16.17" /> \begin{signline}The highway of the upright\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to depart from evil: he that keepeth his way preserveth  his soul.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.16.18" /> \begin{signline}Pride\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}goeth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}before destruction, and an haughty spirit before a fall.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.16.19" /> \begin{signline}Better\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is to be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of an humble spirit with the lowly, than to divide the spoil with the proud.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.16.20" /> \begin{signline}He that handleth a matter wisely shall find good: and whoso trusteth in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, happy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.16.21" /> \begin{signline}The wise in heart shall be called prudent: and the sweetness of the lips increaseth learning.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.16.22" /> \begin{signline}Understanding\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a wellspring of life unto him that hath it: but the instruction of fools\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}folly.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.16.23" /> \begin{signline}The heart of the wise teacheth his mouth, and addeth learning to his lips.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.16.24" /> \begin{signline}Pleasant words\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an honeycomb, sweet to the soul, and health to the bones.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.16.25" /> \begin{signline}There is a way that seemeth right unto a man, but the end thereof\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the ways of death.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.16.26" /> \begin{signline}He that laboureth laboureth for himself; for his mouth craveth it of him.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="27" bcv="PRO.16.27" /> \begin{signline}An ungodly man diggeth up evil: and in his lips\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as a burning fire.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.16.28" /> \begin{signline}A froward man soweth strife: and a whisperer separateth chief friends.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="29" bcv="PRO.16.29" /> \begin{signline}A violent man enticeth his neighbour, and leadeth him into the way\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not good.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="30" bcv="PRO.16.30" /> \begin{signline}He shutteth his eyes to devise froward things: moving his lips he bringeth evil to pass.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="31" bcv="PRO.16.31" /> \begin{signline}The hoary head\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a crown of glory,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}if\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}it be found in the way of righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="32" bcv="PRO.16.32" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}He that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}slow to anger\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better than the mighty; and he that ruleth his spirit than he that taketh a city.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="33" bcv="PRO.16.33" /> \begin{signline}The lot is cast into the lap; but the whole disposing thereof\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="17" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.17.1" /> \begin{signline}Better\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a dry morsel, and quietness therewith, than an house full of sacrifices\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}strife.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.17.2" /> \begin{signline}A wise servant shall have rule over a son that causeth shame, and shall have part of the inheritance among the brethren.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.17.3" /> \begin{signline}The fining pot\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for silver, and the furnace for gold: but the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}trieth the hearts.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.17.4" /> \begin{signline}A wicked doer giveth heed to false lips;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a liar giveth ear to a naughty tongue.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.17.5" /> \begin{signline}Whoso mocketh the poor reproacheth his Maker:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that is glad at calamities shall not be unpunished.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.17.6" /> \begin{signline}Children’s children\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the crown of old men; and the glory of children\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their fathers.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.17.7" /> \begin{signline}Excellent speech becometh not a fool: much less do lying lips a prince.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.17.8" /> \begin{signline}A gift\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a precious stone in the eyes of him that hath it: whithersoever it turneth, it prospereth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.17.9" /> \begin{signline}He that covereth a transgression seeketh love; but he that repeateth a matter separateth \end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}very\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}friends.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.17.10" /> \begin{signline}A reproof entereth more into a wise man than an hundred stripes  into a fool.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.17.11" /> \begin{signline}An evil\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}seeketh  only rebellion: therefore a cruel messenger shall be sent against him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.17.12" /> \begin{signline}Let a bear robbed of her whelps meet a man, rather than a fool in his folly.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.17.13" /> \begin{signline}Whoso rewardeth evil for good, evil shall not depart from his house.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.17.14" /> \begin{signline}The beginning of strife\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}when one letteth out water: therefore leave off contention, before it be meddled with.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.17.15" /> \begin{signline}He that justifieth the wicked, and he that condemneth the just, even they both\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}abomination to the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.17.16" />\begin{signline}Wherefore\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is there\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a price in the hand of a fool to get wisdom, seeing\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he hath\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no heart\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.17.17" /> \begin{signline}A friend loveth at all times, and a brother is born for adversity.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.17.18" /> \begin{signline}A man void of understanding striketh hands,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}becometh surety in the presence of his friend.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.17.19" /> \begin{signline}He loveth transgression that loveth strife:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that exalteth his gate seeketh destruction.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.17.20" /> \begin{signline}He that hath a froward heart findeth no good: and he that hath a perverse tongue falleth into mischief.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.17.21" /> \begin{signline}He that begetteth a fool\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}doeth it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to his sorrow: and the father of a fool hath no joy.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.17.22" /> \begin{signline}A merry heart doeth good\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}like\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a medicine: but a broken spirit drieth the bones.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.17.23" /> \begin{signline}A wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}taketh  a gift out of the bosom to pervert the ways of judgment.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.17.24" /> \begin{signline}Wisdom\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}before him that hath understanding; but the eyes of a fool\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the ends of the earth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.17.25" /> \begin{signline}A foolish son\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a grief to his father, and bitterness to her that bare him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.17.26" /> \begin{signline}Also to punish the just\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not good,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}nor\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to strike princes for equity.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="27" bcv="PRO.17.27" /> \begin{signline}He that hath knowledge spareth his words:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a man of understanding is of an excellent spirit.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.17.28" /> \begin{signline}Even a fool, when he holdeth his peace, is counted wise:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that shutteth his lips\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is esteemed\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a man of understanding.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="18" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.18.1" /> \begin{signline}Through desire a man, having separated himself, seeketh\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}intermeddleth with all wisdom.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.18.2" /> \begin{signline}A fool hath no delight in understanding, but that his heart may discover itself.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.18.3" /> \begin{signline}When the wicked cometh,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}then\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}cometh also contempt, and with ignominy reproach.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.18.4" /> \begin{signline}The words of a man’s mouth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}deep waters,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the wellspring of wisdom\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a flowing brook.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.18.5" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not good to accept the person of the wicked, to overthrow the righteous in judgment.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="6" bcv="PRO.18.6" /> \begin{signline}A fool’s lips enter into contention, and his mouth calleth for strokes.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.18.7" /> \begin{signline}A fool’s mouth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his destruction, and his lips\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the snare of his soul.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.18.8" /> \begin{signline}The words of a talebearer\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as wounds, and they go down into the innermost parts of the belly.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.18.9" /> \begin{signline}He also that is slothful in his work is brother to him that is a great waster.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.18.10" /> \begin{signline}The name of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a strong tower: the righteous runneth into it, and is safe.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.18.11" /> \begin{signline}The rich man’s wealth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his strong city, and as an high wall in his own conceit.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.18.12" /> \begin{signline}Before destruction the heart of man is haughty, and before honour\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}humility.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.18.13" /> \begin{signline}He that answereth a matter before he heareth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, it\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}folly and shame unto him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.18.14" /> \begin{signline}The spirit of a man will sustain his infirmity; but a wounded spirit who can bear?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.18.15" /> \begin{signline}The heart of the prudent getteth knowledge; and the ear of the wise seeketh knowledge.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.18.16" /> \begin{signline}A man’s gift maketh room for him, and bringeth him before great men.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.18.17" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}He that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}first in his own cause\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}seemeth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}just; but his neighbour cometh and searcheth him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.18.18" /> \begin{signline}The lot causeth contentions to cease, and parteth between the mighty.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.18.19" /> \begin{signline}A brother offended\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is harder to be won\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}than a strong city: and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}contentions \end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}like the bars of a castle.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.18.20" /> \begin{signline}A man’s belly shall be satisfied with the fruit of his mouth;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with the increase of his lips shall he be filled.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.18.21" /> \begin{signline}Death and life\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the power of the tongue: and they that love it shall eat the fruit thereof.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.18.22" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Whoso\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}findeth a wife findeth a good\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thing\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and obtaineth favour of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.18.23" /> \begin{signline}The poor useth intreaties; but the rich answereth roughly.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.18.24" /> \begin{signline}A man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that hath\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}friends must shew himself friendly: and there is a friend\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}sticketh closer than a brother.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="19" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.19.1" /> \begin{signline}Better\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the poor that walketh in his integrity, than\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}perverse in his lips, and is a fool.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.19.2" />\begin{signline}Also,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the soul\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}without knowledge,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not good; and he that hasteth with\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}feet sinneth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.19.3" /> \begin{signline}The foolishness of man perverteth his way: and his heart fretteth against the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.19.4" /> \begin{signline}Wealth maketh many friends; but the poor is separated from his neighbour.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.19.5" /> \begin{signline}A false witness shall not be unpunished, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}speaketh lies shall not escape.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="6" bcv="PRO.19.6" /> \begin{signline}Many will intreat the favour of the prince: and every man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a friend to him that giveth gifts.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.19.7" /> \begin{signline}All the brethren of the poor do hate him: how much more do his friends go far from him? he pursueth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them with\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}words,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yet\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}they\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wanting\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to him\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.19.8" /> \begin{signline}He that getteth wisdom loveth his own soul: he that keepeth understanding shall find good.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.19.9" /> \begin{signline}A false witness shall not be unpunished, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}speaketh lies shall perish.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.19.10" /> \begin{signline}Delight is not seemly for a fool; much less for a servant to have rule over princes.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.19.11" /> \begin{signline}The discretion of a man deferreth his anger; and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his glory to pass over a transgression.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.19.12" /> \begin{signline}The king’s wrath\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as the roaring of a lion; but his favour\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as dew upon the grass.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.19.13" /> \begin{signline}A foolish son\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the calamity of his father: and the contentions of a wife\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a continual dropping.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.19.14" /> \begin{signline}House and riches\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the inheritance of fathers: and a prudent wife\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.19.15" /> \begin{signline}Slothfulness casteth into a deep sleep; and an idle soul shall suffer hunger.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.19.16" /> \begin{signline}He that keepeth the commandment keepeth his own soul;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that despiseth his ways shall die.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.19.17" /> \begin{signline}He that hath pity upon the poor lendeth  unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; and that which he hath given will he pay him again.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.19.18" /> \begin{signline}Chasten thy son while there is hope, and let not thy soul spare for his crying.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.19.19" /> \begin{signline}A man of great wrath shall suffer punishment: for if thou deliver\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, yet thou must do it again.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.19.20" /> \begin{signline}Hear counsel, and receive instruction, that thou mayest be wise in thy latter end.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.19.21" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}There are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}many devices in a man’s heart; nevertheless the counsel of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, that shall stand.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.19.22" /> \begin{signline}The desire of a man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his kindness: and a poor man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better than a liar.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.19.23" /> \begin{signline}The fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}tendeth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to life: and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he that hath it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall abide satisfied; he shall not be visited with evil.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.19.24" /> \begin{signline}A slothful\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hideth his hand in\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}bosom, and will not so much as bring it to his mouth again.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.19.25" /> \begin{signline}Smite a scorner, and the simple will beware: and reprove one that hath understanding,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he will understand knowledge.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.19.26" /> \begin{signline}He that wasteth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}father,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}chaseth away\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mother,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a son that causeth shame, and bringeth reproach.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.19.27" /> \begin{signline}Cease, my son, to hear the instruction\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that causeth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to err from the words of knowledge.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.19.28" /> \begin{signline}An ungodly witness scorneth judgment: and the mouth of the wicked devoureth  iniquity.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="29" bcv="PRO.19.29" /> \begin{signline}Judgments are prepared for scorners, and stripes for the back of fools.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="20" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.20.1" /> \begin{signline}Wine\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a mocker, strong drink\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}raging: and whosoever is deceived thereby is not wise.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.20.2" /> \begin{signline}The fear of a king\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as the roaring of a lion:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}whoso\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}provoketh him to anger sinneth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}against\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his own soul.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.20.3" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an honour for a man to cease from strife: but every fool will be meddling.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.20.4" /> \begin{signline}The sluggard will not plow by reason of the cold;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}therefore\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall he beg in harvest, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}have\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}nothing.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.20.5" /> \begin{signline}Counsel in the heart of man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is like\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}deep water; but a man of understanding will draw it out.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.20.6" /> \begin{signline}Most men will proclaim every one his own goodness: but a faithful man who can find?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.20.7" /> \begin{signline}The just\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}walketh  in his integrity: his children\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}blessed after him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.20.8" /> \begin{signline}A king that sitteth in the throne of judgment scattereth away all evil with his eyes.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.20.9" /> \begin{signline}Who can say, I have made my heart clean, I am pure from my sin?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.20.10" /> \begin{signline}Divers weights,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}divers measures, both of them\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}alike abomination to the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.20.11" /> \begin{signline}Even a child is known by his doings, whether his work\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}pure, and whether\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}right.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.20.12" /> \begin{signline}The hearing ear, and the seeing eye, the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}hath made even both of them.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.20.13" /> \begin{signline}Love not sleep, lest thou come to poverty; open thine eyes,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou shalt be satisfied with bread.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.20.14" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}naught,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}naught, saith the buyer: but when he is gone his way, then he boasteth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.20.15" /> \begin{signline}There is gold, and a multitude of rubies: but the lips of knowledge\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a precious jewel.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.20.16" /> \begin{signline}Take his garment that is surety\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a stranger: and take a pledge of him for a strange woman.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.20.17" /> \begin{signline}Bread of deceit\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}sweet to a man; but afterwards his mouth shall be filled with gravel.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.20.18" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Every\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}purpose is established by counsel: and with good advice make war.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.20.19" /> \begin{signline}He that goeth about\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a talebearer revealeth secrets: therefore meddle not with him that flattereth with his lips.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.20.20" /> \begin{signline}Whoso curseth his father or his mother, his lamp shall be put out in obscure darkness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.20.21" /> \begin{signline}An inheritance\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}may be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}gotten hastily at the beginning; but the end thereof shall not be blessed.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.20.22" /> \begin{signline}Say not thou, I will recompense evil;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wait on the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, and he shall save thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.20.23" /> \begin{signline}Divers weights\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an abomination unto the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; and a false balance\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not good.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.20.24" /> \begin{signline}Man’s goings\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}; how can a man then understand his own way?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.20.25" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a snare to the man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}who\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}devoureth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that which is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}holy, and after vows to make enquiry.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.20.26" /> \begin{signline}A wise king scattereth the wicked, and bringeth the wheel over them.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.20.27" /> \begin{signline}The spirit of man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the candle of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, searching all the inward parts of the belly.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.20.28" /> \begin{signline}Mercy and truth preserve the king: and his throne is upholden by mercy.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="29" bcv="PRO.20.29" /> \begin{signline}The glory of young men\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}their strength: and the beauty of old men\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the gray head.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="30" bcv="PRO.20.30" /> \begin{signline}The blueness of a wound cleanseth away evil: so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}do\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}stripes the inward parts of the belly.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="21" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.21.1" /> \begin{signline}The king’s heart\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the hand of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline},\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the rivers of water: he turneth it whithersoever he will.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.21.2" /> \begin{signline}Every way of a man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}right in his own eyes: but the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}pondereth the hearts.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.21.3" /> \begin{signline}To do justice and judgment\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}more acceptable to the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}than sacrifice.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.21.4" /> \begin{signline}An high look, and a proud heart,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the plowing of the wicked,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}sin.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.21.5" /> \begin{signline}The thoughts of the diligent\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}tend\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}only to plenteousness; but of every one\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hasty only to want.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.21.6" /> \begin{signline}The getting of treasures by a lying tongue\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a vanity tossed to and fro of them that seek death.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.21.7" /> \begin{signline}The robbery of the wicked shall destroy them; because they refuse to do judgment.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.21.8" /> \begin{signline}The way of man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}froward and strange: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the pure, his work\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}right.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.21.9" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better to dwell in a corner of the housetop, than with a brawling woman in a wide house.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.21.10" /> \begin{signline}The soul of the wicked desireth evil: his neighbour findeth no favour in his eyes.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.21.11" /> \begin{signline}When the scorner is punished, the simple is made wise: and when the wise is instructed, he receiveth knowledge.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.21.12" /> \begin{signline}The righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wisely considereth the house of the wicked:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but God\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}overthroweth the wicked for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}their\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wickedness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.21.13" /> \begin{signline}Whoso stoppeth his ears at the cry of the poor, he also shall cry himself, but shall not be heard.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.21.14" /> \begin{signline}A gift in secret pacifieth anger: and a reward in the bosom strong wrath.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.21.15" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}joy to the just to do judgment: but destruction\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to the workers of iniquity.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.21.16" /> \begin{signline}The man that wandereth out of the way of understanding shall remain in the congregation of the dead.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.21.17" /> \begin{signline}He that loveth pleasure\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a poor man: he that loveth wine and oil shall not be rich.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.21.18" /> \begin{signline}The wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a ransom for the righteous, and the transgressor for the upright.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.21.19" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better to dwell in the wilderness, than with a contentious and an angry woman.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.21.20" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}There is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}treasure to be desired and oil in the dwelling of the wise; but a foolish man spendeth it up.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.21.21" /> \begin{signline}He that followeth after righteousness and mercy findeth life, righteousness, and honour.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.21.22" /> \begin{signline}A wise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}scaleth  the city of the mighty, and casteth down the strength of the confidence thereof.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.21.23" /> \begin{signline}Whoso keepeth his mouth and his tongue keepeth his soul from troubles.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.21.24" /> \begin{signline}Proud\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}haughty scorner\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his name, who dealeth in proud wrath.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="25" bcv="PRO.21.25" /> \begin{signline}The desire of the slothful killeth him; for his hands refuse to labour.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.21.26" /> \begin{signline}He coveteth greedily all the day long: but the righteous giveth and spareth not.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.21.27" /> \begin{signline}The sacrifice of the wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}abomination: how much more,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he bringeth it with a wicked mind?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.21.28" /> \begin{signline}A false witness shall perish: but the man that heareth speaketh constantly.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="29" bcv="PRO.21.29" /> \begin{signline}A wicked man hardeneth his face: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the upright, he directeth his way.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="30" bcv="PRO.21.30" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}There is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no wisdom nor understanding nor counsel against the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="31" bcv="PRO.21.31" /> \begin{signline}The horse\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}prepared  against the day of battle: but safety\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="22" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.22.1" />\begin{signline}A\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}good\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}name\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}rather to be chosen than great riches,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}loving favour rather than silver and gold.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.22.2" /> \begin{signline}The rich and poor meet together: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the maker of them all.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.22.3" /> \begin{signline}A prudent\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}foreseeth  the evil, and hideth himself: but the simple pass on, and are punished.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.22.4" /> \begin{signline}By humility\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}riches, and honour, and life.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.22.5" /> \begin{signline}Thorns\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}snares\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the way of the froward: he that doth keep his soul shall be far from them.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.22.6" /> \begin{signline}Train up a child in the way he should go: and when he is old, he will not depart from it.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.22.7" /> \begin{signline}The rich ruleth over the poor, and the borrower\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}servant to the lender.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.22.8" /> \begin{signline}He that soweth iniquity shall reap vanity: and the rod of his anger shall fail.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.22.9" /> \begin{signline}He that hath a bountiful eye shall be blessed; for he giveth of his bread to the poor.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.22.10" /> \begin{signline}Cast out the scorner, and contention shall go out; yea, strife and reproach shall cease.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.22.11" /> \begin{signline}He that loveth pureness of heart,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the grace of his lips the king\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his friend.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.22.12" /> \begin{signline}The eyes of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}preserve knowledge, and he overthroweth the words of the transgressor.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.22.13" /> \begin{signline}The slothful\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}saith,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}There is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a lion without, I shall be slain in the streets.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.22.14" /> \begin{signline}The mouth of strange women\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a deep pit: he that is abhorred of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall fall therein.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.22.15" /> \begin{signline}Foolishness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}bound in the heart of a child;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the rod of correction shall drive it far from him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.22.16" /> \begin{signline}He that oppresseth the poor to increase his\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}riches, and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that giveth to the rich,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}surely\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}come\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to want.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="17" bcv="PRO.22.17" /> \begin{signline}Bow down thine ear, and hear the words of the wise, and apply thine heart unto my knowledge.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.22.18" />\begin{signline}For\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a pleasant thing if thou keep them within thee; they shall withal be fitted in thy lips.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.22.19" /> \begin{signline}That thy trust may be in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, I have made known to thee this day, even to thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.22.20" /> \begin{signline}Have not I written to thee excellent things in counsels and knowledge,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.22.21" /> \begin{signline}That I might make thee know the certainty of the words of truth; that thou mightest answer the words of truth to them that send unto thee?\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="22" bcv="PRO.22.22" /> \begin{signline}Rob not the poor, because he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}poor: neither oppress the afflicted in the gate:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.22.23" /> \begin{signline}For the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}will plead their cause, and spoil the soul of those that spoiled them.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="24" bcv="PRO.22.24" /> \begin{signline}Make no friendship with an angry man; and with a furious man thou shalt not go:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.22.25" /> \begin{signline}Lest thou learn his ways, and get a snare to thy soul.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="26" bcv="PRO.22.26" />\begin{signline}Be not thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}one\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of them that strike hands,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}or\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}of them that are sureties for debts.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.22.27" /> \begin{signline}If thou hast nothing to pay, why should he take away thy bed from under thee?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.22.28" /> \begin{signline}Remove not the ancient landmark, which thy fathers have set.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="29" bcv="PRO.22.29" /> \begin{signline}Seest thou a man diligent in his business? he shall stand before kings; he shall not stand before mean\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="23" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.23.1" /> \begin{signline}When thou sittest to eat with a ruler, consider diligently what\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}before thee:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.23.2" /> \begin{signline}And put a knife to thy throat, if thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a man given to appetite.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.23.3" /> \begin{signline}Be not desirous of his dainties: for they\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}deceitful meat.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="4" bcv="PRO.23.4" /> \begin{signline}Labour not to be rich: cease from thine own wisdom.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.23.5" /> \begin{signline}Wilt thou set thine eyes upon that which is not? for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}riches\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}certainly make themselves wings; they fly away as an eagle toward heaven.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="6" bcv="PRO.23.6" /> \begin{signline}Eat thou not the bread of\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him that hath\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an evil eye, neither desire thou his dainty meats:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.23.7" /> \begin{signline}For as he thinketh in his heart, so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he: Eat and drink, saith he to thee; but his heart\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not with thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.23.8" /> \begin{signline}The morsel\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou hast eaten shalt thou vomit up, and lose thy sweet words.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.23.9" /> \begin{signline}Speak not in the ears of a fool: for he will despise the wisdom of thy words.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="10" bcv="PRO.23.10" /> \begin{signline}Remove not the old landmark; and enter not into the fields of the fatherless:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.23.11" /> \begin{signline}For their redeemer\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mighty; he shall plead their cause with thee.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="12" bcv="PRO.23.12" /> \begin{signline}Apply thine heart unto instruction, and thine ears to the words of knowledge.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.23.13" /> \begin{signline}Withhold not correction from the child: for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}if\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou beatest him with the rod, he shall not die.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.23.14" /> \begin{signline}Thou shalt beat him with the rod, and shalt deliver his soul from hell.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.23.15" /> \begin{signline}My son, if thine heart be wise, my heart shall rejoice, even mine.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.23.16" /> \begin{signline}Yea, my reins shall rejoice, when thy lips speak right things.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="17" bcv="PRO.23.17" /> \begin{signline}Let not thine heart envy sinners: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be thou\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the fear of the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}all the day long.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.23.18" /> \begin{signline}For surely there is an end; and thine expectation shall not be cut off.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="19" bcv="PRO.23.19" /> \begin{signline}Hear thou, my son, and be wise, and guide thine heart in the way.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.23.20" /> \begin{signline}Be not among winebibbers; among riotous eaters of flesh:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.23.21" /> \begin{signline}For the drunkard and the glutton shall come to poverty: and drowsiness shall clothe\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}a man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with rags.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.23.22" /> \begin{signline}Hearken unto thy father that begat thee, and despise not thy mother when she is old.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.23.23" /> \begin{signline}Buy the truth, and sell\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}also\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wisdom, and instruction, and understanding.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.23.24" /> \begin{signline}The father of the righteous shall greatly rejoice: and he that begetteth a wise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}child\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall have joy of him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.23.25" /> \begin{signline}Thy father and thy mother shall be glad, and she that bare thee shall rejoice.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.23.26" /> \begin{signline}My son, give me thine heart, and let thine eyes observe my ways.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.23.27" /> \begin{signline}For a whore\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a deep ditch; and a strange woman\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a narrow pit.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.23.28" /> \begin{signline}She also lieth in wait as\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a prey, and increaseth the transgressors among men.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="29" bcv="PRO.23.29" /> \begin{signline}Who hath woe? who hath sorrow? who hath contentions? who hath babbling? who hath wounds without cause? who hath redness of eyes?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="30" bcv="PRO.23.30" /> \begin{signline}They that tarry long at the wine; they that go to seek mixed wine.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="31" bcv="PRO.23.31" /> \begin{signline}Look not thou upon the wine when it is red, when it giveth his colour in the cup,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}when\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}it moveth itself aright.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="32" bcv="PRO.23.32" /> \begin{signline}At the last it biteth like a serpent, and stingeth like an adder.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="33" bcv="PRO.23.33" /> \begin{signline}Thine eyes shall behold strange women, and thine heart shall utter perverse things.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="34" bcv="PRO.23.34" /> \begin{signline}Yea, thou shalt be as he that lieth down in the midst of the sea, or as he that lieth upon the top of a mast.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="35" bcv="PRO.23.35" /> \begin{signline}They have stricken me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shalt thou say, and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I was not sick; they have beaten me,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}I felt\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not: when shall I awake? I will seek it yet again.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="24" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.24.1" /> \begin{signline}Be not thou envious against evil men, neither desire to be with them.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.24.2" /> \begin{signline}For their heart studieth destruction, and their lips talk of mischief.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="3" bcv="PRO.24.3" /> \begin{signline}Through wisdom is an house builded; and by understanding it is established:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.24.4" /> \begin{signline}And by knowledge shall the chambers be filled with all precious and pleasant riches.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.24.5" /> \begin{signline}A wise man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}strong; yea, a man of knowledge increaseth  strength.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.24.6" /> \begin{signline}For by wise counsel thou shalt make thy war: and in multitude of counsellors\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}safety.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="7" bcv="PRO.24.7" /> \begin{signline}Wisdom\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}too high for a fool: he openeth not his mouth in the gate.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.24.8" /> \begin{signline}He that deviseth to do evil shall be called a mischievous person.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.24.9" /> \begin{signline}The thought of foolishness\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}sin: and the scorner\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an abomination to men.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.24.10" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}If\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thou faint in the day of adversity, thy strength\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}small.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="11" bcv="PRO.24.11" /> \begin{signline}If thou forbear to deliver\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them that are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}drawn unto death, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}those that are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}ready to be slain;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.24.12" /> \begin{signline}If thou sayest, Behold, we knew it not; doth not he that pondereth the heart consider \end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}? and he that keepeth thy soul, doth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}not\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he know\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}? and shall\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}not\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he render to\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}every\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}man according to his works?\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="13" bcv="PRO.24.13" /> \begin{signline}My son, eat thou honey, because\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good; and the honeycomb,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}sweet to thy taste:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.24.14" />\begin{signline}So\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the knowledge of wisdom\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unto thy soul: when thou hast found\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, then there shall be a reward, and thy expectation shall not be cut off.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="15" bcv="PRO.24.15" /> \begin{signline}Lay not wait, O wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, against the dwelling of the righteous; spoil not his resting place:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.24.16" /> \begin{signline}For a just\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}falleth seven times, and riseth up again: but the wicked shall fall into mischief.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="17" bcv="PRO.24.17" /> \begin{signline}Rejoice not when thine enemy falleth, and let not thine heart be glad when he stumbleth:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.24.18" /> \begin{signline}Lest the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}see\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and it displease him, and he turn away his wrath from him.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="19" bcv="PRO.24.19" /> \begin{signline}Fret not thyself because of evil\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, neither be thou envious at the wicked;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.24.20" /> \begin{signline}For there shall be no reward to the evil\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man;\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the candle of the wicked shall be put out.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="21" bcv="PRO.24.21" /> \begin{signline}My son, fear thou the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}and the king:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}meddle not with them that are given to change:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.24.22" /> \begin{signline}For their calamity shall rise suddenly; and who knoweth the ruin of them both?\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="23" bcv="PRO.24.23" />\begin{signline}These\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}also\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}belong\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to the wise.\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not good to have respect of persons in judgment.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.24.24" /> \begin{signline}He that saith unto the wicked, Thou\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}art\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}righteous; him shall the people curse, nations shall abhor him:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.24.25" /> \begin{signline}But to them that rebuke\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}him\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall be delight, and a good blessing shall come upon them.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.24.26" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Every man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall kiss\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}lips that giveth a right answer.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.24.27" /> \begin{signline}Prepare thy work without, and make it fit for thyself in the field; and afterwards build thine house.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="28" bcv="PRO.24.28" /> \begin{signline}Be not a witness against thy neighbour without cause; and deceive\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}not\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}with thy lips.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="29" bcv="PRO.24.29" /> \begin{signline}Say not, I will do so to him as he hath done to me: I will render to the man according to his work.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="30" bcv="PRO.24.30" /> \begin{signline}I went by the field of the slothful, and by the vineyard of the man void of understanding;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="31" bcv="PRO.24.31" /> \begin{signline}And, lo, it was all grown over with thorns,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}nettles had covered the face thereof, and the stone wall thereof was broken down.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="32" bcv="PRO.24.32" /> \begin{signline}Then I saw,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}considered\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}well: I looked upon\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it, and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}received instruction.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="33" bcv="PRO.24.33" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Yet\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a little sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands to sleep:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="34" bcv="PRO.24.34" /> \begin{signline}So shall thy poverty come\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}one that travelleth; and thy want as an armed man.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="25" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.25.1" />\begin{signline}These\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}also proverbs of Solomon, which the men of Hezekiah king of Judah copied out.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="2" bcv="PRO.25.2" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the glory of God to conceal a thing: but the honour of kings\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to search out a matter.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.25.3" /> \begin{signline}The heaven for height, and the earth for depth, and the heart of kings\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}unsearchable.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="4" bcv="PRO.25.4" /> \begin{signline}Take away the dross from the silver, and there shall come forth a vessel for the finer.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.25.5" /> \begin{signline}Take away the wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}from\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}before the king, and his throne shall be established in righteousness.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="6" bcv="PRO.25.6" /> \begin{signline}Put not forth thyself in the presence of the king, and stand not in the place of great\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men:\end{signline}</add>
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.25.7" /> \begin{signline}For better\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that it be said unto thee, Come up hither; than that thou shouldest be put lower in the presence of the prince whom thine eyes have seen.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="8" bcv="PRO.25.8" /> \begin{signline}Go not forth hastily to strive, lest\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thou know not\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}what to do in the end thereof, when thy neighbour hath put thee to shame.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.25.9" /> \begin{signline}Debate thy cause with thy neighbour\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}himself;\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}and discover not a secret to another:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.25.10" /> \begin{signline}Lest he that heareth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}put thee to shame, and thine infamy turn not away.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="11" bcv="PRO.25.11" /> \begin{signline}A word fitly spoken\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is like\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}apples of gold in pictures of silver.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.25.12" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}As\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an earring of gold, and an ornament of fine gold,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a wise reprover upon an obedient ear.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.25.13" /> \begin{signline}As the cold of snow in the time of harvest,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a faithful messenger to them that send him: for he refresheth the soul of his masters.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.25.14" /> \begin{signline}Whoso boasteth himself of a false gift\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is like\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}clouds and wind without rain.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.25.15" /> \begin{signline}By long forbearing is a prince persuaded, and a soft tongue breaketh the bone.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.25.16" /> \begin{signline}Hast thou found honey? eat so much as is sufficient for thee, lest thou be filled therewith, and vomit it.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.25.17" /> \begin{signline}Withdraw thy foot from thy neighbour’s house; lest he be weary of thee, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hate thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.25.18" /> \begin{signline}A man that beareth false witness against his neighbour\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a maul, and a sword, and a sharp arrow.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.25.19" /> \begin{signline}Confidence in an unfaithful man in time of trouble\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is like\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a broken tooth, and a foot out of joint.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.25.20" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}As\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that taketh away a garment in cold weather,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}vinegar upon nitre, so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that singeth songs to an heavy heart.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="21" bcv="PRO.25.21" /> \begin{signline}If thine enemy be hungry, give him bread to eat; and if he be thirsty, give him water to drink:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.25.22" /> \begin{signline}For thou shalt heap coals of fire upon his head, and the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall reward thee.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.25.23" /> \begin{signline}The north wind driveth away rain: so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}doth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an angry countenance a backbiting tongue.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.25.24" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better to dwell in the corner of the housetop, than with a brawling woman and in a wide house.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.25.25" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}As\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}cold waters to a thirsty soul, so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good news from a far country.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.25.26" /> \begin{signline}A righteous man falling down before the wicked\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a troubled fountain, and a corrupt spring.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.25.27" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not good to eat much honey: so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to search their own glory\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is not\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}glory.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.25.28" /> \begin{signline}He that\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}hath\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no rule over his own spirit\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is like\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a city\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}broken down,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}without walls.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="26" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.26.1" /> \begin{signline}As snow in summer, and as rain in harvest, so honour is not seemly for a fool.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.26.2" /> \begin{signline}As the bird by wandering, as the swallow by flying, so the curse causeless shall not come.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.26.3" /> \begin{signline}A whip for the horse, a bridle for the ass, and a rod for the fool’s back.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="4" bcv="PRO.26.4" /> \begin{signline}Answer not a fool according to his folly, lest thou also be like unto him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.26.5" /> \begin{signline}Answer a fool according to his folly, lest he be wise in his own conceit.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="6" bcv="PRO.26.6" /> \begin{signline}He that sendeth a message by the hand of a fool cutteth off the feet,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}drinketh damage.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.26.7" /> \begin{signline}The legs of the lame are not equal: so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a parable in the mouth of fools.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.26.8" /> \begin{signline}As he that bindeth a stone in a sling, so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that giveth honour to a fool.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.26.9" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}As\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a thorn goeth up into the hand of a drunkard, so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a parable in the mouth of fools.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.26.10" /> \begin{signline}The great\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}God\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}that formed all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}both rewardeth the fool, and rewardeth transgressors.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.26.11" /> \begin{signline}As a dog returneth to his vomit,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a fool returneth to his folly.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.26.12" /> \begin{signline}Seest thou a man wise in his own conceit?\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}more hope of a fool than of him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.26.13" /> \begin{signline}The slothful\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}saith,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}There is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a lion in the way; a lion\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in the streets.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.26.14" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}As\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the door turneth  upon his hinges, so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}doth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the slothful upon his bed.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.26.15" /> \begin{signline}The slothful hideth his hand in\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}bosom; it grieveth him to bring it again to his mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.26.16" /> \begin{signline}The sluggard\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wiser in his own conceit than seven men that can render a reason.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.26.17" /> \begin{signline}He that passeth by,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}meddleth with strife\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}belonging\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not to him,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is like\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}one that taketh a dog by the ears.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="18" bcv="PRO.26.18" /> \begin{signline}As a mad\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}who casteth firebrands, arrows, and death,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.26.19" />\begin{signline}So\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}deceiveth his neighbour, and saith, Am not I in sport?\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="20" bcv="PRO.26.20" /> \begin{signline}Where no wood is,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the fire goeth out: so where\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no talebearer, the strife ceaseth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.26.21" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}As\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}coals\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to burning coals, and wood to fire; so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a contentious man to kindle strife.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.26.22" /> \begin{signline}The words of a talebearer\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}as wounds, and they go down into the innermost parts of the belly.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.26.23" /> \begin{signline}Burning lips and a wicked heart\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are like\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a potsherd covered with silver dross.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="24" bcv="PRO.26.24" /> \begin{signline}He that hateth dissembleth with his lips, and layeth up deceit within him;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.26.25" /> \begin{signline}When he speaketh fair, believe him not: for\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}seven abominations in his heart.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.26.26" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}Whose\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hatred is covered by deceit, his wickedness shall be shewed before the\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}whole\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}congregation.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.26.27" /> \begin{signline}Whoso diggeth a pit shall fall therein: and he that rolleth a stone, it will return upon him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.26.28" /> \begin{signline}A lying tongue hateth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}those that are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}afflicted by it; and a flattering mouth worketh ruin.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="27" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.27.1" /> \begin{signline}Boast not thyself of to morrow; for thou knowest not what a day may bring forth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.27.2" /> \begin{signline}Let another man praise thee, and not thine own mouth; a stranger, and not thine own lips.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="3" bcv="PRO.27.3" /> \begin{signline}A stone\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}heavy, and the sand weighty; but a fool’s wrath\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}heavier than them both.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.27.4" /> \begin{signline}Wrath\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}cruel, and anger\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}outrageous; but who\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}able to stand before envy?\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="5" bcv="PRO.27.5" /> \begin{signline}Open rebuke\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better than secret love.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.27.6" /> \begin{signline}Faithful\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the wounds of a friend; but the kisses of an enemy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}deceitful.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.27.7" /> \begin{signline}The full soul loatheth an honeycomb; but to the hungry soul every bitter thing is sweet.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.27.8" /> \begin{signline}As a bird that wandereth from her nest, so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a man that wandereth from his place.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="9" bcv="PRO.27.9" /> \begin{signline}Ointment and perfume rejoice the heart: so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}doth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the sweetness of a man’s friend by hearty counsel.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.27.10" /> \begin{signline}Thine own friend, and thy father’s friend, forsake not; neither go into thy brother’s house in the day of thy calamity:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}better\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a neighbour\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}near than a brother far off.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.27.11" /> \begin{signline}My son, be wise, and make my heart glad, that I may answer him that reproacheth me.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.27.12" /> \begin{signline}A prudent\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}foreseeth the evil,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hideth himself;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the simple pass on,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}are punished.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.27.13" /> \begin{signline}Take his garment that is surety for a stranger, and take a pledge of him for a strange woman.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.27.14" /> \begin{signline}He that blesseth his friend with a loud voice, rising early in the morning, it shall be counted a curse to him.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="15" bcv="PRO.27.15" /> \begin{signline}A continual dropping in a very rainy day and a contentious woman are alike.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.27.16" /> \begin{signline}Whosoever hideth her hideth the wind, and the ointment of his right hand,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}bewrayeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}itself\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.27.17" /> \begin{signline}Iron sharpeneth iron; so a man sharpeneth the countenance of his friend.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.27.18" /> \begin{signline}Whoso keepeth the fig tree shall eat the fruit thereof: so he that waiteth on his master shall be honoured.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.27.19" /> \begin{signline}As in water face\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}answereth\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to face, so the heart of man to man.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.27.20" /> \begin{signline}Hell and destruction are never full; so the eyes of man are never satisfied.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.27.21" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}As\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the fining pot for silver, and the furnace for gold; so\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a man to his praise.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.27.22" /> \begin{signline}Though thou shouldest bray a fool in a mortar among wheat with a pestle,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yet\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}will not his foolishness depart from him.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="23" bcv="PRO.27.23" /> \begin{signline}Be thou diligent to know the state of thy flocks,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}look well to thy herds.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.27.24" /> \begin{signline}For riches\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not for ever: and doth the crown\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}endure\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}to every generation?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.27.25" /> \begin{signline}The hay appeareth, and the tender grass sheweth itself, and herbs of the mountains are gathered.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.27.26" /> \begin{signline}The lambs\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}for thy clothing, and the goats\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the price of the field.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.27.27" />\begin{signline}And\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thou shalt have\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}goats’ milk enough for thy food, for the food of thy household, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}for\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the maintenance for thy maidens.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="28" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.28.1" /> \begin{signline}The wicked flee when no man pursueth: but the righteous are bold as a lion.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.28.2" /> \begin{signline}For the transgression of a land many\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the princes thereof: but by a man of understanding\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}and\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}knowledge the state\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thereof\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall be prolonged.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.28.3" /> \begin{signline}A poor man that oppresseth the poor\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is like\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a sweeping rain which leaveth no food.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.28.4" /> \begin{signline}They that forsake the law praise the wicked: but such as keep the law contend with them.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.28.5" /> \begin{signline}Evil men understand not judgment: but they that seek the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}understand all\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.28.6" /> \begin{signline}Better\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the poor that walketh in his uprightness, than\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}perverse\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}ways, though he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}rich.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.28.7" /> \begin{signline}Whoso keepeth the law\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a wise son: but he that is a companion of riotous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shameth his father.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.28.8" /> \begin{signline}He that by usury and unjust gain increaseth his substance, he shall gather it for him that will pity the poor.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.28.9" /> \begin{signline}He that turneth away his ear from hearing the law, even his prayer\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}shall be\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}abomination.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.28.10" /> \begin{signline}Whoso causeth the righteous to go astray in an evil way, he shall fall himself into his own pit: but the upright shall have good\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}in possession.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.28.11" /> \begin{signline}The rich man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wise in his own conceit; but the poor that hath understanding searcheth him out.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.28.12" /> \begin{signline}When righteous\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}do rejoice,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}great glory: but when the wicked rise, a man is hidden.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.28.13" /> \begin{signline}He that covereth his sins shall not prosper: but whoso confesseth and forsaketh\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall have mercy.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.28.14" /> \begin{signline}Happy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the man that feareth alway: but he that hardeneth his heart shall fall into mischief.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.28.15" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}As\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a roaring lion, and a ranging bear;\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}so is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a wicked ruler over the poor people.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.28.16" /> \begin{signline}The prince that wanteth understanding\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}also a great oppressor:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he that hateth covetousness shall prolong\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}days.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.28.17" /> \begin{signline}A man that doeth violence to the blood of\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}any\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}person shall flee to the pit; let no man stay him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.28.18" /> \begin{signline}Whoso walketh uprightly shall be saved: but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}perverse\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}ways shall fall at once.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.28.19" /> \begin{signline}He that tilleth his land shall have plenty of bread: but he that followeth after vain\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}persons\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}shall have poverty enough.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.28.20" /> \begin{signline}A faithful man shall abound with blessings: but he that maketh haste to be rich shall not be innocent.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.28.21" /> \begin{signline}To have respect of persons\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not good: for for a piece of bread\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}man will transgress.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.28.22" /> \begin{signline}He that hasteth to be rich\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}hath\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an evil eye, and considereth not that poverty shall come upon him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.28.23" /> \begin{signline}He that rebuketh a man afterwards shall find more favour than he that flattereth with the tongue.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.28.24" /> \begin{signline}Whoso robbeth his father or his mother, and saith,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no transgression; the same\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the companion of a destroyer.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.28.25" /> \begin{signline}He that is of a proud heart stirreth up strife: but he that putteth his trust in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall be made fat.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.28.26" /> \begin{signline}He that trusteth in his own heart is a fool: but whoso walketh wisely, he shall be delivered.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.28.27" /> \begin{signline}He that giveth unto the poor shall not lack: but he that hideth his eyes shall have many a curse.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.28.28" /> \begin{signline}When the wicked rise, men hide themselves: but when they perish, the righteous increase.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="29" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.29.1" /> \begin{signline}He, that being often reproved hardeneth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}neck, shall suddenly be destroyed, and that without remedy.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.29.2" /> \begin{signline}When the righteous are in authority, the people rejoice: but when the wicked beareth rule, the people mourn. \end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.29.3" /> \begin{signline}Whoso loveth wisdom rejoiceth his father: but he that keepeth company with harlots spendeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}substance.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.29.4" /> \begin{signline}The king by judgment establisheth the land: but he that receiveth gifts overthroweth it.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.29.5" /> \begin{signline}A man that flattereth his neighbour spreadeth a net for his feet.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.29.6" /> \begin{signline}In the transgression of an evil man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a snare: but the righteous doth sing and rejoice.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.29.7" /> \begin{signline}The righteous considereth the cause of the poor:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the wicked regardeth not to know\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.29.8" /> \begin{signline}Scornful men bring a city into a snare: but wise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}men\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}turn away wrath.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.29.9" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}If\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a wise man contendeth with a foolish man, whether he rage or laugh,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no rest.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="10" bcv="PRO.29.10" /> \begin{signline}The bloodthirsty hate the upright: but the just seek his soul.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.29.11" /> \begin{signline}A fool uttereth all his mind: but a wise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}man\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}keepeth it in till afterwards.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.29.12" /> \begin{signline}If a ruler hearken to lies, all his servants\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.29.13" /> \begin{signline}The poor and the deceitful man meet together: the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}lighteneth both their eyes.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.29.14" /> \begin{signline}The king that faithfully judgeth the poor, his throne shall be established for ever.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.29.15" /> \begin{signline}The rod and reproof give wisdom: but a child left\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}to himself\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}bringeth his mother to shame.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.29.16" /> \begin{signline}When the wicked are multiplied, transgression increaseth: but the righteous shall see their fall.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.29.17" /> \begin{signline}Correct thy son, and he shall give thee rest; yea, he shall give delight unto thy soul.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.29.18" />\begin{signline}Where\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no vision, the people perish: but he that keepeth the law, happy\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}he.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.29.19" /> \begin{signline}A servant will not be corrected by words: for though he understand he will not answer.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.29.20" /> \begin{signline}Seest thou a man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}hasty in his words?\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}more hope of a fool than of him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.29.21" /> \begin{signline}He that delicately bringeth up his servant from a child shall have him become\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}son at the length.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.29.22" /> \begin{signline}An angry man stirreth up strife, and a furious man aboundeth in transgression.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.29.23" /> \begin{signline}A man’s pride shall bring him low: but honour shall uphold the humble in spirit.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.29.24" /> \begin{signline}Whoso is partner with a thief hateth  his own soul: he heareth cursing, and bewrayeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.29.25" /> \begin{signline}The fear of man bringeth a snare: but whoso putteth his trust in the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd> \begin{signline}shall be safe.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.29.26" /> \begin{signline}Many seek the ruler’s favour; but\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}every\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}man’s judgment\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}cometh\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}from the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.29.27" /> \begin{signline}An unjust man\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}an abomination to the just: and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}he that is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}upright in the way\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}abomination to the wicked.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="30" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.30.1" /> \begin{signline}The words of Agur the son of Jakeh,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}even\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the prophecy: the man spake unto Ithiel, even unto Ithiel and Ucal,\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.30.2" />\begin{signline}Surely I\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}am\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}more brutish than\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}any\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}man, and have not the understanding of a man.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.30.3" /> \begin{signline}I neither learned wisdom, nor have the knowledge of the holy.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.30.4" /> \begin{signline}Who hath ascended up into heaven, or descended? who hath gathered the wind in his fists? who hath bound the waters in a garment? who hath established all the ends of the earth? what\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his name, and what\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}his son’s name, if thou canst tell?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.30.5" /> \begin{signline}Every word of God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}pure: he\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a shield unto them that put their trust in him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.30.6" /> \begin{signline}Add thou not unto his words, lest he reprove thee, and thou be found a liar.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="7" bcv="PRO.30.7" /> \begin{signline}Two\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}have I required of thee; deny me\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}them\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not before I die:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.30.8" /> \begin{signline}Remove far from me vanity and lies: give me neither poverty nor riches; feed me with food convenient for me:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.30.9" /> \begin{signline}Lest I be full, and deny\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}thee\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and say, Who\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}? or lest I be poor, and steal, and take the name of my God\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}in vain\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="10" bcv="PRO.30.10" /> \begin{signline}Accuse not a servant unto his master, lest he curse thee, and thou be found guilty.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.30.11" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}There is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a generation\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}curseth their father, and doth not bless their mother.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.30.12" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}There is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a generation\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}pure in their own eyes, and\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yet\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}is not washed from their filthiness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.30.13" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}There is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a generation, O how lofty are their eyes! and their eyelids are lifted up.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.30.14" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}There is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a generation, whose teeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}swords, and their jaw teeth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}as\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}knives, to devour the poor from off the earth, and the needy from\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}among\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}men.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="15" bcv="PRO.30.15" /> \begin{signline}The horseleach hath two daughters,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}crying\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, Give, give. There are three\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}are never satisfied,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}yea\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, four\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}say not,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}enough:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.30.16" /> \begin{signline}The grave; and the barren womb; the earth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}is not filled with water; and the fire\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}saith not,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}enough.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.30.17" /> \begin{signline}The eye\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mocketh  at\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}father, and despiseth to obey\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}his\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}mother, the ravens of the valley shall pick it out, and the young eagles shall eat it.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="18" bcv="PRO.30.18" /> \begin{signline}There be three\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}are too wonderful for me, yea, four which I know not:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.30.19" /> \begin{signline}The way of an eagle in the air; the way of a serpent upon a rock; the way of a ship in the midst of the sea; and the way of a man with a maid.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.30.20" />\begin{signline}Such\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the way of an adulterous woman; she eateth, and wipeth her mouth, and saith, I have done no wickedness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.30.21" /> \begin{signline}For three\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the earth is disquieted, and for four\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}it cannot bear:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.30.22" /> \begin{signline}For a servant when he reigneth; and a fool when he is filled with meat;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.30.23" /> \begin{signline}For an odious\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}woman\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}when she is married; and an handmaid that is heir to her mistress.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="24" bcv="PRO.30.24" /> \begin{signline}There be four\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things which are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}little upon the earth, but they\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}exceeding wise:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.30.25" /> \begin{signline}The ants\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a people not strong, yet they prepare their meat in the summer;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.30.26" /> \begin{signline}The conies\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a feeble folk, yet make they their houses in the rocks;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.30.27" /> \begin{signline}The locusts have no king, yet go they forth all of them by bands;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.30.28" /> \begin{signline}The spider taketh hold with her hands, and is in kings’ palaces.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="29" bcv="PRO.30.29" /> \begin{signline}There be three\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}things\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}which go well, yea, four are comely in going:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="30" bcv="PRO.30.30" /> \begin{signline}A lion\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}which is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}strongest among beasts, and turneth not away for any;\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="31" bcv="PRO.30.31" /> \begin{signline}A greyhound; an he goat also; and a king, against whom\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}there is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}no rising up.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="32" bcv="PRO.30.32" /> \begin{signline}If thou hast done foolishly in lifting up thyself, or if thou hast thought evil,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}lay\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}thine hand upon thy mouth.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="33" bcv="PRO.30.33" /> \begin{signline}Surely the churning of milk bringeth forth butter, and the wringing of the nose bringeth forth blood: so the forcing of wrath bringeth forth strife.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><c id="31" />
<p><v id="1" bcv="PRO.31.1" /> \begin{signline}The words of king Lemuel, the prophecy that his mother taught him.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="2" bcv="PRO.31.2" /> \begin{signline}What, my son? and what, the son of my womb? and what, the son of my vows?\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="3" bcv="PRO.31.3" /> \begin{signline}Give not thy strength unto women, nor thy ways to that which destroyeth kings.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="4" bcv="PRO.31.4" /> \begin{signline}\end{signline}<add>\begin{signline}It is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not for kings, O Lemuel,\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}not for kings to drink wine; nor for princes strong drink:\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="5" bcv="PRO.31.5" /> \begin{signline}Lest they drink, and forget the law, and pervert the judgment of any of the afflicted.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="6" bcv="PRO.31.6" /> \begin{signline}Give strong drink unto him that is ready to perish, and wine unto those that be of heavy hearts.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="7" bcv="PRO.31.7" /> \begin{signline}Let him drink, and forget his poverty, and remember his misery no more.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="8" bcv="PRO.31.8" /> \begin{signline}Open thy mouth for the dumb in the cause of all such as are appointed to destruction.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="9" bcv="PRO.31.9" /> \begin{signline}Open thy mouth, judge righteously, and plead the cause of the poor and needy.\end{signline}
<ve /></p><p><v id="10" bcv="PRO.31.10" />\begin{signline}¶ Who can find a virtuous woman? for her price\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}far above rubies.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="11" bcv="PRO.31.11" /> \begin{signline}The heart of her husband doth safely trust in her, so that he shall have no need of spoil.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="12" bcv="PRO.31.12" /> \begin{signline}She will do him good and not evil all the days of her life.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="13" bcv="PRO.31.13" /> \begin{signline}She seeketh wool, and flax, and worketh willingly with her hands.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="14" bcv="PRO.31.14" /> \begin{signline}She is like the merchants’ ships; she bringeth her food from afar.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="15" bcv="PRO.31.15" /> \begin{signline}She riseth also while it is yet night, and giveth meat to her household, and a portion to her maidens.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="16" bcv="PRO.31.16" /> \begin{signline}She considereth a field, and buyeth it: with the fruit of her hands she planteth a vineyard.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="17" bcv="PRO.31.17" /> \begin{signline}She girdeth her loins with strength, and strengtheneth her arms.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="18" bcv="PRO.31.18" /> \begin{signline}She perceiveth that her merchandise\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}good: her candle goeth not out by night.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="19" bcv="PRO.31.19" /> \begin{signline}She layeth her hands to the spindle, and her hands hold the distaff.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="20" bcv="PRO.31.20" /> \begin{signline}She stretcheth out her hand to the poor; yea, she reacheth forth her hands to the needy.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="21" bcv="PRO.31.21" /> \begin{signline}She is not afraid of the snow for her household: for all her household\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}clothed with scarlet.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="22" bcv="PRO.31.22" /> \begin{signline}She maketh herself coverings of tapestry; her clothing\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}silk and purple.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="23" bcv="PRO.31.23" /> \begin{signline}Her husband is known in the gates, when he sitteth among the elders of the land.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="24" bcv="PRO.31.24" /> \begin{signline}She maketh fine linen, and selleth\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}it;\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}and delivereth girdles unto the merchant.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="25" bcv="PRO.31.25" /> \begin{signline}Strength and honour\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}are\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}her clothing; and she shall rejoice in time to come.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="26" bcv="PRO.31.26" /> \begin{signline}She openeth her mouth with wisdom; and in her tongue\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}the law of kindness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="27" bcv="PRO.31.27" /> \begin{signline}She looketh well to the ways of her household, and eateth not the bread of idleness.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="28" bcv="PRO.31.28" /> \begin{signline}Her children arise up, and call her blessed; her husband\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}also\end{signline}</add>\begin{signline}, and he praiseth her.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="29" bcv="PRO.31.29" /> \begin{signline}Many daughters have done virtuously, but thou excellest them all.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="30" bcv="PRO.31.30" /> \begin{signline}Favour\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}deceitful, and beauty\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}is\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}vain:\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}but\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}a woman\end{signline} <add>\begin{signline}that\end{signline}</add> \begin{signline}feareth the\end{signline} <nd>\begin{signline}LORD\end{signline}</nd>\begin{signline}, she shall be praised.\end{signline}
<ve /><v id="31" bcv="PRO.31.31" /> \begin{signline}Give her of the fruit of her hands; and let her own works praise her in the gates.\end{signline}
<ve /></p></book>
